What is a Professional Apprenticeship?

Salary:
$50-60k starting salary
â€¢ **INTERESTED? APPLY NOW TO LEARN MORE!***

What Does a Data Analyst Do?
A data analyst is a person whose job is to gather and interpret data in order to solve a specific problem. The role includes plenty of time spent with data but entails communicating findings too.
Hereâ€™s what many data analysts do on a day-to-day basis:

- Gather data: Analysts often collect data themselves. This could include conducting surveys, tracking visitor characteristics on a company website, or buying datasets from data collection specialists.
- Clean data: Raw data might contain duplicates, errors, or outliers. Cleaning the data means maintaining the quality of data in a spreadsheet or through a programming language so that your interpretations wonâ€™t be wrong or skewed.
- Model data: This entails creating and designing the structures of a database. You might choose what types of data to store and collect, establish how data categories are related to each other, and work through how the data actually appears.
- Interpret data: Interpreting data will involve finding patterns or trends in data that could answer the question at hand.
- Present: Communicating the results of your findings will be a key part of your job. You do this by putting together visualizations like charts and graphs, writing reports, and presenting information to interested parties.
â€¢ *APPLY NOW TO LEARN MORE!***
A member of our team will reach out to share more information on the program and next steps to formally apply for the apprenticeship.
Applications will be open through August 8, 2023

title: Sr. Market Data Reporting Analyst
description:
Job Description:

The Regulatory Services Division of the National Association of Insurance Commissioners (NAIC) has an exciting opportunity for a Sr. Market Data Reporting Analyst. We are looking for a team member who would enjoy working for an organization that strives every day to support the public good and make a difference. This position would be responsible for supporting the MARS emails... MAC, MCAS production, MCAS blanks and CSV assistant creation, CDS and RIRS systems to ensure that the data is appropriately loaded to the NAIC databases. Upholding the data quality of the identified systems to ensure the data shared with other state insurance departments is of good quality.

This position is based out of the NAIC's state-of-the-art offices in Town Pavilion in the heart of downtown Kansas City which includes great restaurants and top-notch entertainment venues. This is a full-time remote position, within 100 miles of the office and in-office requirements as scheduled, in a positive and flexible environment.

State/Company Support/Analysis
â€¢ Develops and maintains excellent working relationship with state contacts.
â€¢ Completes thorough analysis and corresponds with state contacts to:
â€¢ Ensures data files from states are loading to the NAIC MIS database by close of business on the day they are received.
â€¢ Ensures data accuracy, completeness, quality and to prevent data anomalies.
â€¢ Ensures timely receipt of MIS data for systems and states as assigned and work with states that are not sending MIS data regularly.
â€¢ Maintains good understanding of state contacts interaction with MIS systems, such as RIRS, MATS and MARS.
â€¢ Identify alternate methods of transmitting data if current processes are unstable.
â€¢ Completes in depth error analysis for MIS systems and supported states as assigned.
â€¢ Gathers and documents state-specific information regarding states procedures for handling MIS data and corresponding biographic and demographic data.
â€¢ Contacts companies and states to determine the reason for inconsistent MCAS reporting.
â€¢ Documents correspondence with companies and states regarding filing decisions, exceptions, and compliance.

System Support/Analysis
â€¢ Monitors status of systems, and ensure readers are up and running for processing data files.
â€¢ Generates files via Linux commands and inclusion of raw data. This may require modification of data files provided within other environments and loading them into common arch staging tables.
â€¢ Works with common arch developers to resolve coding issues, test data anomalies and ensure data quality.
â€¢ Maintains a good understanding of the forms used to represent exams, CDS, RIRS and 1033 data and the MIS data model
â€¢ Performs a review of insurance company Market Conduct Annual Statement (MCAS) filings and amendments.
â€¢ Resolves MCAS filing problems with the company and state contacts by evaluating reporting requirements against problems encountered using prior experience and/or applying technical knowledge of the MCAS filing process and systems.
â€¢ Analyzes the validation checks in Market Conduct System (MCS) and Insurance Data Repository (IDR) and review the report output for validity, completeness, and accuracy.
â€¢ Ensures that the MCAS data, validation and results tables are current and reflect all changes approved for MCAS.
â€¢ Performs in-depth manual testing of the MCAS Application.
â€¢ Documents the creation of new lines of business. Ensures appropriate supporting documentation that is created, verified and posted to the MCAS Webpage.
â€¢ Creates and maintains the MCAS Webpage, along with the supporting content.

General Analysis/Communication
â€¢ Analyzes errors and data inconsistencies using internally developed applications, raw data file analysis and SQL queries.
â€¢ Independently builds simple and complex SQL queries.
â€¢ Works with common arch development staff to review errors documented in the logs to determine development changes needed, and completes analysis of modified common arch code based on the behavior of the data.
â€¢ Builds working relationships and works closely with vendors (SBS and Sircon) in gathering business rules and requirements to complete mapping documents to create a smooth coding and testing process.
â€¢ Communicates state implementations, business rule changes, and mapping/coding changes.
â€¢ Establishes target project completion dates for new states implementations and conversions. Creates and communicates project timelines with all interested parties to ensure the target production date is met.
â€¢ Maintains a historic to current file for each assigned state to include an updated list of state contacts, frequency of production files from states, data discrepancy issues, systems upgrades, and any additional applicable data quality or enhancement documentation via Metrics.
â€¢ Provides excellent customer service for business partners and MIS Team and must provide timely response to any inquiries.
â€¢ Operates the Market Regulation/MCAS Help Desk by answering questions, escalating issues to support staff for handling, as needed, and following up to ensure all requests are addressed in a timely fashion.
â€¢ Advises and provides knowledge of market conduct processes, requirements, and reporting to NAIC members, NAIC staff, insurance companies and other interested parties based on MCAS knowledge and experience.
â€¢ Assists with the documentation, evaluation of CDS & RIRS data in the Enterprise Data Platform Project. Ensures that documentation fulfills the needs of our Insurance Regulators.

Secondary Functions:
â€¢ Advises and educates state regulators on database and technological enhancements that may increase the integrity and quality of data submissions as well as create an easier method of submitting data to the NAIC databases.
â€¢ Creates and updates educational tutorials, newsletters, and documentation.
â€¢ Recommends system modification to increase the quality of the collected data.
â€¢ Updates all MCAS help manuals and instruction guides as needed.
â€¢ Performs a general review of the Blanks Agenda for content and impact to the market conduct annual statement applications and brings any concerns to the attention of the Market Analysis Manager and Assistant Director of Market Regulation.
â€¢ Provides knowledge to the Market Regulation Trainer in development/enhancement of training vehicles associated with market applications and processes.
â€¢ Develops and maintains good understanding of the business rules and systems used to process MIS data and its relationship with Producer Licensing.
â€¢ Acts as a Lead for other analysts.
â€¢ Assists with onboarding and training of analysts.
â€¢ Develops and maintains excellent rapport with business partners and programmers, and management teams; represents MIS Team and Project Manager when necessary.
â€¢ Responds to special data requests from Industry, Consumers or States. This could require the creation of complex queries, verification of legal compliance and data integrity.
â€¢ Performs audits at the end of each MIS systems conversion, reload or code change and provide analysis to the state.
â€¢ Other duties may be assigned.

Education and/or experience required:

Bachelor's degree (B.A.) from four-year college or university and 5+ years of Data Analytics experience; or an equivalent combination of education and work experience.

Skills and Abilities:
â€¢ Ability to solve practical problems and deal with a variety of concreate variables in the resolution.
â€¢ Ability to interpret a variety of instructions furnished in written, oral, diagram or schedule form.
â€¢ Work experience with Microsoft Windows, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Access.
â€¢ Required experience with SQL+, and/or Oracle.
â€¢ Ability to work in a team environment.
â€¢ Requires obtaining and maintaining a good working knowledge of the Market systems
â€¢ Must have experience in reviewing, validation and/or building transaction-based data for troubleshooting and testing of updated systems.
â€¢ Must be highly detail oriented.
â€¢ Excellent customer service skills.
â€¢ Mentoring, training and presentation skills preferred.
â€¢ Familiarity with insurance regulatory community preferred

Compensation:

$54,145 - $65,000, to be commensurate with education and experience.

title: Public Health Data Analyst - Hybrid
description:
Job Title: Public Health Data Analyst

Job Location: Atlanta, GA...

Job Category: Public Health

BACKGROUND

Rumph & Associates is seeking experienced Public Health Data Analysts. Works within the public health sector to gather and analyze data on infectious diseases. Uses raw data to search for trends, patterns, and strategies that can improve public health. Present findings to leadership to use the information in presentations. Other responsibilities include maintaining databases and accessing data as needed.

MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES
â€¢ Convert existing datasets from a diverse array of file formats (e.g., Microsoft Excel, Access, and SQL) into analytic datasets.
â€¢ Manages, manipulates, and transforms data stored in a variety of file formats such as SAS datasets, Microsoft Access, Microsoft Excel, and SQL.
â€¢ Provide data cleaning and management support for surveillance and research analyses. Contribute to production of study summaries or manuscripts for publication.
â€¢ Ensure the security and confidentiality of analytical data files and provide data file documentation describing the scientific data source.
â€¢ Perform data quality assurance activities, including identifying and resolving any inconsistencies in data flow, data outside legitimate ranges, and illogical data responses by developing data quality reports and investigation and resolution of data anomalies or errors by using a combination of software packages including SAS or R, MS Access and Excel, and other software as warranted. Track completeness and quality of data over time.
â€¢ Compile and merge individual-level data submitted from multiple external partners in diverse data formats.
â€¢ Explore the use of data visualization platforms (e.g., R, Power BI, mapping software) to quickly summarize study findings. Support data visualization activities (both for hypothesis generation and to share data with the response).
â€¢ Develop communication materials such as slide sets and summary reports.
â€¢ Perform daily/weekly data runs and create daily/weekly reports. Troubleshoot issues with daily/weekly data runs. Work on an ongoing basis to improve and automate code. Conduct weekly data cleaning and generate weekly error reports.
â€¢ Determine sampling methodologies to implement if case counts exceed certain thresholds. Characterize surveillance back-fill to help with real-time interpretation of data. Gather study team requirements and translate them into technical specifications for SAS programs.
â€¢ Program SAS data validation checks and listings to identify data discrepancies.
â€¢ Program SAS checks to integrate and reconcile data from US states and US Territories.
â€¢ Edit data sets as required to prepare for analysis.
â€¢ Produce prevalence estimates and placing the estimates in tables, via SQL and EXCEL.
â€¢ Develop and/ or modify software to perform data analysis and prepare both routine and ad hoc reports.
â€¢ Document and troubleshoot software.

EDUCATION, REQUIREMENTS, AND MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS

Education/Required Qualifications:
â€¢ Bachelorâ€™s degree in a science, public health or statistical-related field and 5 yearsâ€™ experience in public health data analysis OR a Masterâ€™s degree in Information Technology - related field with 3-5 yearsâ€™ experience in public health, epidemiology, or statistical analysis.
â€¢ Expertise with SQL and complex algorithms.
â€¢ Experience with advanced statistical software packages, Macros, STAT, GRAPH.
â€¢ Experience with PC/LAN versions of SAS is essential.
â€¢ Familiarity with established statistical methodologies in the health sciences, particularly those related to chronic disease, behavioral based, and immunization surveillance and data analysis.
â€¢ Knowledge of efficient strategies for analysis of large data sets, including techniques for merging datasets from diverse sources is required and knowledge of weighting of data is desirable.
â€¢ Ability to communicate effectively with public health scientists and program staff on mathematical and statistical topics is required.
â€¢ Experience with Microsoft Office products such as Word, Excel, Outlook, PowerBI, etc. and statistical analysis tools including STATA, SPSS, SUDAN, and other software packages as needed for statistical analysis and graphing.
â€¢ Applied SAS Output Delivery System (ODS) for generating summary reports, enhancing output to non-SAS data files, and generating HTML web for outputs.
â€¢ Excellent data visualization, written, and oral presentation skills.
â€¢ Ability to manage multiple projects at one time and prioritize work to customer satisfaction.
â€¢ Language Proficiency: Fluent English (Level IV) reading, speaking, and writing ability is required.

Application Instructions: Please send one combined document (MS Word or PDF) that includes all the below items to: Rumph & Associates, P.C. Please be sure to label the subject line of the e-mail â€œPublic Health Data Analyst.â€

description:

We have already launched our own Enterprise Data Hub, the digital backbone of this company, and we need more leaders in the data analytics discipline who are forward thinking, self-guided and innovative to continue to build out the hub across our lines of business, integrating all of our data, mastering data and focusing on data quality to fundamentally shift the way Charles River operates through data science and advanced analytics.

The following are responsibilities related to the Master Data Analyst:
â€¢ Create and manage Master Data elements (Business Partners, Customer, Materials/products, Vendors, BOMs, Recipes, Resources, Cost Centers, GL accounts, Profit centers) across MDM and ERP Systems, serving as subject matter expert.

â€¢ Partner with colleagues and other functional teams on opportunities to reduce data errors.
â€¢ Work with Sales, Finance and Operations groups to continually improve processes.
â€¢ Maintain an understanding of source data and appropriate data ownership, governance and stewardship.
â€¢ Serve as a tester for MDM system changes/enhancements.
â€¢ Create and ensure adherence to current processes and update these where required
â€¢ Develop exceptional, accountable relationships with key stakeholders

Job Qualifications

The following are minimum requirements related to the Master Data Analyst position.
â€¢ Education: Bachelorâ€™s or masterâ€™s degree from accredited university in Computer Science, Data Management, Business Administration or equivalent program.
â€¢ Experience: 5+ years of relevant experience in Master Data Management experience
â€¢ 5+ years of experience in Microsoft Excel, Word, and PowerPoint with strong digital literacy with proficiency
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in S/4 HANA, SAP ECC and other ERP systems
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in master data and SAP (preferably Customer Master, Vendor Master, Material Master, Pricing, Business Partners, GL accounts, Cost Centers, Profit centers, BOMS, Recipes, Resources).
â€¢ Ability to create and update LSMW, Winshuttle or S/4 migration cockpit (LTMC) scripts to support high volume requests
â€¢ Experience with CVI (Customer Vendor Integration) for S/4 HANA
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in business analysis and/or project experience.
â€¢ Experience in regulatory compliance.
â€¢ Execute in Master Data migration strategies associated with new Mergers and or Acquisitions for large scale transformation and M&A efforts.
â€¢ Strong organizational and prioritization skills
â€¢ Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Ability to understand and troubleshoot sophisticated business problems.
â€¢ Detail oriented
â€¢ Excellent interpersonal, written and oral communication skills.
â€¢ Ability to work both independently and as part of a team and deliver with tight deadlines.
â€¢ Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle multi tasks.
â€¢ An equivalent combination of education and experience may be accepted as a satisfactory substitute for the specific education and experience listed above.
â€¢ Approximately 30% travel required for project deployments at various CRL sites

The following are strongly desired:
â€¢ Agile experience particularly as Product Owner or leading some ceremonies such as standups, sprint planning, sprint retrospectives, and backlog grooming
â€¢ Certified Data Steward
â€¢ Experience in Life Sciences industry with master data
â€¢ Strong intellectual curiosity, eager to learn new technologies and adapt solutions for automation.

Compensation Data

The pay range for this position is $65,000 - $75,000 USD. Please note that salaries vary within the range based on factors including, but not limited to, experience, skills, education, certifications, and location.

About Corporate Functions

The Corporate Functions provide operational support across Charles River in areas such as Human Resources, Finance, IT, Legal, Sales, Quality Assurance, Marketing, and Corporate Development. They partner with their colleagues across the company to develop and drive strategies and to set global standards. The functions are essential to providing a bridge between strategic vision and operational readiness, to ensure ongoing functional innovation and capability improvement

description:

Thereâ€™s never been a more exciting time to be on the Enterprise Data Analytics team at Charles River Labs! We are on a mission to make the Enterprise Data Analytics team be the backbone of todayâ€™s business, as data-driven decision-making enables business leaders to make informed choices quickly to boost revenue, improve productivity, and stay a step ahead of the market. We have already launched our own Enterprise Data Hub, the digital backbone of this company, and we need more leaders in the data analytics discipline who are forward thinking, self-guided and innovative to continue to build out the hub across our lines of business, integrating all of our data, mastering data and focusing on data quality to fundamentally shift the way Charles River operates through data science and advanced analytics.

The following are responsibilities related to the Master Data Analyst:
â€¢ Create and manage Master Data elements (Business Partners, Customer, Materials/products, Vendors, BOMs, Recipes, Resources, Cost Centers, GL accounts, Profit centers) across MDM and ERP Systems, serving as subject matter expert.

â€¢ Lead the development and/or update, deploy, and align Master Data standards across geographies and business areas.

â€¢ Provide the training and support to all colleagues in creating and understanding use of data within ERP and operational systems.

â€¢ Partner with colleagues and other functional teams on opportunities to reduce data errors.
â€¢ Work with Sales, Finance and Operations groups to continually improve processes.
â€¢ Maintain an understanding of source data and appropriate data ownership, governance and stewardship.
â€¢ Serve as a tester for MDM system changes/enhancements.
â€¢ Create and ensure adherence to current processes and update these where required
â€¢ Develop exceptional, accountable relationships with key stakeholders

Job Qualifications

The following are minimum requirements related to the Master Data Analyst position.
â€¢ Education: Bachelorâ€™s or masterâ€™s degree from accredited university in Computer Science, Data Management, Business Administration or equivalent program.
â€¢ Experience: 5+ years of relevant experience in Master Data Management experience
â€¢ 5+ years of experience in Microsoft Excel, Word, and PowerPoint with strong digital literacy with proficiency
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in S/4 HANA, SAP ECC and other ERP systems
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in master data and SAP (preferably Customer Master, Vendor Master, Material Master, Pricing, Business Partners, GL accounts, Cost Centers, Profit centers, BOMS, Recipes, Resources).
â€¢ Ability to create and update LSMW, Winshuttle or S/4 migration cockpit (LTMC) scripts to support high volume requests
â€¢ Experience with CVI (Customer Vendor Integration) for S/4 HANA
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in business analysis and/or project experience.
â€¢ Experience in regulatory compliance.
â€¢ Execute in Master Data migration strategies associated with new Mergers and or Acquisitions for large scale transformation and M&A efforts.
â€¢ Strong organizational and prioritization skills
â€¢ Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Ability to understand and troubleshoot sophisticated business problems.
â€¢ Detail oriented
â€¢ Excellent interpersonal, written and oral communication skills.
â€¢ Ability to work both independently and as part of a team and deliver with tight deadlines.
â€¢ Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle multi tasks.
â€¢ An equivalent combination of education and experience may be accepted as a satisfactory substitute for the specific education and experience listed above.
â€¢ Approximately 30% travel required for project deployments at various CRL sites

The following are strongly desired:
â€¢ Agile experience particularly as Product Owner or leading some ceremonies such as standups, sprint planning, sprint retrospectives, and backlog grooming
â€¢ Certified Data Steward
â€¢ Experience in Life Sciences industry with master data
â€¢ Strong intellectual curiosity, eager to learn new technologies and adapt solutions for automation.

Compensation Data

The pay range for this position is $65,000 - $75,000 USD. Please note that salaries vary within the range based on factors including, but not limited to, experience, skills, education, certifications, and location.

About Corporate Functions

The Corporate Functions provide operational support across Charles River in areas such as Human Resources, Finance, IT, Legal, Sales, Quality Assurance, Marketing, and Corporate Development. They partner with their colleagues across the company to develop and drive strategies and to set global standards. The functions are essential to providing a bridge between strategic vision and operational readiness, to ensure ongoing functional innovation and capability improvement

description:

Thereâ€™s never been a more exciting time to be on the Enterprise Data Analytics team at Charles River Labs! We are on a mission to make the Enterprise Data Analytics team be the backbone of todayâ€™s business, as data-driven decision-making enables business leaders to make informed choices quickly to boost revenue, improve productivity, and stay a step ahead of the market. We have already launched our own Enterprise Data Hub, the digital backbone of this company, and we need more leaders in the data analytics discipline who are forward thinking, self-guided and innovative to continue to build out the hub across our lines of business, integrating all of our data, mastering data and focusing on data quality to fundamentally shift the way Charles River operates through data science and advanced analytics.

The following are responsibilities related to the Master Data Analyst:

â€¢ Work with Sales, Finance and Operations groups to continually improve processes.
â€¢ Maintain an understanding of source data and appropriate data ownership, governance and stewardship.
â€¢ Serve as a tester for MDM system changes/enhancements.
â€¢ Create and ensure adherence to current processes and update these where required
â€¢ Develop exceptional, accountable relationships with key stakeholders

Job Qualifications

The following are minimum requirements related to the Master Data Analyst position.
â€¢ Education: Bachelorâ€™s or masterâ€™s degree from accredited university in Computer Science, Data Management, Business Administration or equivalent program.
â€¢ Experience: 5+ years of relevant experience in Master Data Management experience
â€¢ 5+ years of experience in Microsoft Excel, Word, and PowerPoint with strong digital literacy with proficiency
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in S/4 HANA, SAP ECC and other ERP systems
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in master data and SAP (preferably Customer Master, Vendor Master, Material Master, Pricing, Business Partners, GL accounts, Cost Centers, Profit centers, BOMS, Recipes, Resources).
â€¢ Ability to create and update LSMW, Winshuttle or S/4 migration cockpit (LTMC) scripts to support high volume requests
â€¢ Experience with CVI (Customer Vendor Integration) for S/4 HANA
â€¢ 2+ years of experience in business analysis and/or project experience.
â€¢ Experience in regulatory compliance.
â€¢ Execute in Master Data migration strategies associated with new Mergers and or Acquisitions for large scale transformation and M&A efforts.
â€¢ Strong organizational and prioritization skills
â€¢ Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Ability to understand and troubleshoot sophisticated business problems.
â€¢ Detail oriented
â€¢ Excellent interpersonal, written and oral communication skills.
â€¢ Ability to work both independently and as part of a team and deliver with tight deadlines.
â€¢ Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle multi tasks.
â€¢ An equivalent combination of education and experience may be accepted as a satisfactory substitute for the specific education and experience listed above.

The following are strongly desired:
â€¢ Agile experience particularly as Product Owner or leading some ceremonies such as standups, sprint planning, sprint retrospectives, and backlog grooming
â€¢ Certified Data Steward
â€¢ Experience in Life Sciences industry with master data
â€¢ Strong intellectual curiosity, eager to learn new technologies and adapt solutions for automation.

Compensation Data

The pay range for this position is $65,000 - $75,000 USD. Please note that salaries vary within the range based on factors including, but not limited to, experience, skills, education, certifications, and location.

About Corporate Functions

The Corporate Functions provide operational support across Charles River in areas such as Human Resources, Finance, IT, Legal, Sales, Quality Assurance, Marketing, and Corporate Development. They partner with their colleagues across the company to develop and drive strategies and to set global standards. The functions are essential to providing a bridge between strategic vision and operational readiness, to ensure ongoing functional innovation and capability improvement

description: Data Analyst Summary Apex Health Solutions is leading a healthcare transformation through our partnerships with physicians and healthcare insurers. Through our unique models, Apex empowers physicians to truly manage a patientâ€™s health, delivering high quality, affordable care in a modern, patient focused approach. The Data Analyst is responsible for data extraction, data mining, data profiling... and data source to target mapping activities using SQL. The Data Analyst will work closely with business subject matter experts and engineers to operationalize business processes using data, in support of data integrations and warehousing projects. In this role, the Data Analyst will play a critical role in connecting our partners and enabling our critical solutions through Apexâ€™s use of actionable data and empowering processes through harmonized data across the entire spectrum from care provision, claim payment and process visibility. Join our fast-paced, experienced team of healthcare leaders and re-shape healthcare! Essential Functions Write SQL scripts to analyze, validate, or correct data according to requirements, which may include complex stored procedures, views, and functions. Perform data extraction, data mining, and data profiling activities. Profile data sets for completeness and validity, and build automated SQL scripts to assess completeness, validity, and other data metrics. Analyze and pull data as well as measure, monitor, review, analyze, and troubleshoot data quality issues using SQL. Convert existing datasets from a diverse array of file formats, including Excel, Access, SQL, ASCII, text files, etc., into analytic datasets. title: Data Analyst I
description:
GENERAL SUMMARY/

OVERVIEW STATEMENT...

The NeuroValue Lab is seeking a full-time Data Analyst to provide analytic support for research activities within the Department of Neurology, Massachusetts General Hospital (MGH).

The MGH NeuroValue lab focuses on health services and outcomes research, specifically assessing the economic burden associated with neurological conditions.
The lab was created to increase the value of healthcare in neurology with respect to the ratio of quality and/or outcomes to cost ). Reporting to Dr.

Lidia Moura, M.D., M.P.H., Director MGH NeuroValue, the Data Analyst will contribute largely to the analytical components of ongoing studies.
These studies will produce generalizable, publishable findings.

Specifically, the Data Analyst will work with a team of investigators, clinical research coordinators and analysts on various clinical studies and quality improvement projects.

The Data Analyst will be responsible for translating research questions into analytic plans; analyzing clinical data, conducting valid statistical tests and statistical models; and assisting with data visualization and communicating findings in presentations and manuscripts.
We are looking for someone with training in biostatistics, epidemiology, statistics, or a related field. Analytical experience using Electronic Health Record (EHR) data, longitudinal data, and advanced clinical statistical models is preferred.

Specific tasks will include:
database management, data extraction, data cleaning/quality checks, and conducting statistical analysis using linked and/or multiple data sources

PRINCIPAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
The Data Analyst will be working directly under the supervision of Dr. Moura on various data focused tasks including, but not limited to, data cleaning, data harmonization, data quality control, and data analysis and interpretation (e.g. multivariate regression analyses, survival analyses, etc.).

The Data Analyst may also be asked to assist in conducting literature reviews, developing grant proposals, and developing presentations and manuscripts for dissemination of findings.

Qualifications SKILLS/ABILITIES/COMPETENCIES REQUIRED:

The ideal candidate will have achieved strong performance in college-level statistics courses, with demonstrated strong analytic ability (including at least some experience working in SAS, STATA, R, Python, or similar programming languages).
This position requires attention to detail, especially in ensuring data security, quality and accuracy.

The ability to work simultaneously on various tasks, to maintain attention to detail, and to effectively contribute to the project team are also essential.

EDUCATION:
Bachelor's Degree Required, with some background in statistics or related field

EXPERIENCE:
At least some demonstrated experience working in SAS, SPSS, R, Python, or other programming language is required, as is a desire to learn more about data analysis

WORKING CONDITIONS:
Onsite. EEO Statement Massachusetts General Hospital is an Equal Opportunity Employer. By embracing diverse skills, perspectives and ideas, we choose to lead. Applications from protected veterans and individuals with disabilities are strongly encouraged

title: Clinical Data Analyst
description:
We're a Little Different

Our mission is clear. We bring to life a healing ministry through our compassionate care and exceptional service...
At Mercy, we believe in careers that match the unique gifts of unique individuals â€“ careers that not only make the most of your skills and talents, but also your heart. Join us and discover why Modern Healthcare Magazine named us in its "Top 100 Places to Work."

Overview:

The Clinical Quality Outcomes team is a dynamic group with clinical, technical and financial experience that partners with leaders across the Ministry.
Our team leverages its expertise with interpretation of quality measures, new payment models, statistical analysis, data modeling, visualization development and electronic health record data mining to achieve the purpose statement of the Mercy Quality and Safety department:
Mercy Quality and Safety will drive high reliability outcomes, accountability, clinical excellence and remove unnecessary variation. The effective alignment of people, processes and technology will provide the best care to our patients by eliminating harm and realizing the quadruple aim.

title: Sr. IT Business Analyst
description:
GDH had partnered with an enterprise company that is actively looking for a Sr. IT Business Analyst. You will be responsible for pulling value from data by working with assigned business units to understand opportunities where data solutions can support business objectives, improve process efficiency, or support data driven decision making. To deliver on these opportunities, the Senior IT... Business Data Analyst analyzes business requirements and associated data, and provides subject matter expertise on systems, data, and business processes to teams tasked with building data solutions. To mitigate risks associated with data usage, the Senior IT Business Data Analyst facilitates data and BI stewardship to ensure data is used consistently and accurately throughout the organization, leading to confident decisions based on trusted data. Additionally, Senior IT Business Data Analysts develop BI data models as well as BI applications (e.g. reports, dashboards, data visualizations) to enable valuable usage of data assets. As a senior member of the Data Analyst team, the Senior IT Business Data Analyst assists the Data Engineering Manager in development of new processes, templates, and mentoring of less experienced analysts.
Responsibilities:

a. Develop, enhance, and support BI models and applications (e.g., reports, dashboards, data visualizations) in support of customer needs in assigned business areas.

b. Partner with assigned business areas to ensure that BI applications and workspaces are optimized for business purpose and aligned with relevant data governance policies.

c. Gather and forward customer feedback and suggestions for product improvement.

a. Resolve BI issues utilizing excellent customer service, problem solving, and technical thinking/reasoning skills following established support process and metrics guidelines.

b. Measure and analyze incoming issues to determine root cause and develop technical and training solutions to minimize reoccurrences and severity; report results to management.

c. Accurately document all customer issues, resolution steps, and gather feedback in support tracking software to enhance identifying and reporting trends leading to recurring problems.

d. Develop and publish support documentation for internal users for troubleshooting, training and other areas as needed.

e. Primary BI technology stack in use is Microsoft, which includes SSAS, SSRS, Power BI, and Excel BI components. Other technologies could be required due to changing business or technical needs.

d. Reach and maintain proficiency in all technologies relevant to position. Learn new features as they become available in technology stack utilized by Data Analyst team,

e. Stay current on emerging industry capabilities related to data management and business intelligence that could provide ongoing value to assigned business units.

f. Analyze and document requirements as well as current state reporting, business rules, and other variables relevant to building proposed data solutions.

g. Assist PTOs and developers building data solutions by clarifying business intelligence requirements and performing quality assurance (QA) testing of published data sets, ensuring accuracy and adherence to business rules.

h. Act as Data PTO when needed with support of Data Engineering Manager to support team workload. Provide leadership to less experienced team members on projects as well as user workgroups (centers of excellence).

i. Capture and maintain information for Data Inventory as well as metadata for published data sets.

j. Assist the team with the design processes and develop supporting materials such as document templates to assist Data Analyst team in effective support of the companyâ€™s data strategy.

k. Could also include researching how technology could be better leveraged by analyst team (e.g. Azure DevOps, SharePoint, etc.) and performing implementation tasks.

â€¢ Have a high degree of comfort with rapidly changing ambiguous contexts and an ability to help chart a clear path forward in these contexts.

description:
Responsibilities

Enterprise Data Center Service Desk Tier 2 Analyst...

Overview:

We are seeking a Technical Assistance Center (TAC) Analyst to
â€¢ Support US Marine Corps (USMC) enterprise-level data center operations
â€¢ Enable management, monitoring, incident response and management for USMC application hosting environment for world-wide customers
What you will do...

As a TAC (Tier 2 Service Desk) Analyst you will be responsible for ensuring operations and security of critical infrastructure supporting worldwide USMC operations. The TAC Analyst is responsible for managing, monitoring, responding to incidents, and supporting the hybrid cloud datacenter infrastructure and hosted application administrators for the USMC enterprise application hosting environment

Responsibilities include:
â€¢ Execution of hybrid cloud data center TAC processes, functions, activities and tasks.
â€¢ Performs: Incident Management, Event Management, Request Fulfillment, Platform Patching, ITSM Queue Management, Bridge Management, Call Center Management actions.
â€¢ Serves as the initial triage and resolution point for all shift-based activities and performs: resolution, escalation or recall actions and activities as directed by SOP or Service Desk Shift Lead.
â€¢ Provides assistance in triage, troubleshooting, remediation, restoral of service for enterprise datacenter systems (on-prem and cloud) including Windows/Linux Servers, CISCO and VMWare NSX networking equipment, SQL/Oracle databases, VMWare Virtualization systems (ESXi, vSphere, vCenter, vROPS/Aria, NSX-T, etc), NetBackup, NetApp & Unity storage, and facilities equipment/systems.
â€¢ Assists in preparing for and executing shift transition with oncoming and off going Shift Lead, ensuring an comprehensive and orderly transfer of knowledge, schedule, equipment, tasks and activities across shift roles.
â€¢ Executes Service Desk Battle Rhythm activities and assigned activities: Data Center Equipment Checks, COP Monitoring, Platform Patch Preparation/Execution, Database and Platform Backup Initiation, Preventative Maintenance on Data Center equipment, services and applications, Customer/Stakeholder Notification, etc.).
â€¢ Supports Enterprise Information System-EIS Tier I requirements including EIS (SharePoint) account management, troubleshooting, and script/report requirements.
â€¢ DAY SHIFT position, 4 days per week, 10 hour shift

Qualifications

â€¢ BS 2-4 Years, or MS 0-2, will consider HS 6-8

â€¢ Knowledge and experience with Microsoft Windows Server, Microsoft SharePoint, RHEL, LAN/WAN networking, Proxy/Reverse Proxy, VMWare virtualization environments, VMWare Operations Management Suite, Log Management tools, NetBackup, Microsoft SQL, Oracle, VSphere, Active Directory/Directory Services, HP Server Automation (or similar Enterprise Platform patching tool), and ACAS
â€¢ Specific expertise in ITSM, Incident Management, Event Management, Knowledge Management, Problem Management, Customer Service and Data Center technologies.
â€¢ US Citizen, must possess an active SECRET Clearance

title: Data Analyst , Value-based Care Services Client Analytics
description:
How will this role have an impact?

The Data Analyst contributes to the overall success of our organization by applying data mining techniques and statistical modeling to population health data to better understand cost, utilization, and quality of care for a defined patient population typically part of an Accountable Care Organizations (ACO) or similar environments. Through analyzing patient... claims, EHR, and organizational data, the Healthcare Data Analyst will contribute to identifying progress, performance, and opportunities for improvement on program, financial, quality, patient experience, and other metrics. The analytic findings will help healthcare providers in various value-based and pay-for-performance programs understand and identify methods to maximize reimbursement and improve population health. This work contributes to the development of new strategies and tactics to improve overall health care delivery and transform rural health systems across the country as they adapt from volume-based to value-based models of care.

This role will report to our Director, Analytics for VBC Client Analytics.

What will you do?
â€¢ Prepare a variety of reports including statistical analyses for stakeholders to assist with decision-making and tracking accountability.
â€¢ Respond to Ad hoc reporting requests by creating reports as needed for specific situations.
â€¢ Develop new reports, dashboards and other means to enable transparency and to monitor system-wide performance of program progress, total cost of care and clinical quality.
â€¢ Monitor trend of cost, utilization and quality of care for a defined patient population, identify factors driving the changes, and predict future trends.
â€¢ Support acquisition and implementation of new information sources, data collection strategies, data governance, and analytics.
â€¢ Help staff with data manipulation and analytic methods to improve analytic deliverables when required.
â€¢ Other duties as assigned.

We Are Looking For Someone With
â€¢ Bachelorâ€™s Degree with concentration in health informatics, computing, epidemiology, statistics, or related field
â€¢ 3-5 years relevant experience.
â€¢ Strong SQL, Python, or R skills, ability to perform effective querying involving multiple tables and subqueries. Experience with SQL and Power BI strongly preferred.
â€¢ Ability to examine, interpret and report results of analytical initiatives to stakeholders.
â€¢ Preferred understanding of health data formats including Medicare claims, EMR, ADT feeds, lab and pharmacy. Previous experience analyzing medical claims or EMR data is strongly preferred
â€¢ Excellent oral and written communication skills; ability to present complex information in an understandable and compelling manner

About Us

Signify Health is helping build the healthcare system we all want to experience by transforming the home into the healthcare hub. We coordinate care holistically across individualsâ€™ clinical, social, and behavioral needs so they can enjoy more healthy days at home. By building strong connections to primary care providers and community resources, weâ€™re able to close critical care and social gaps, as well as manage risk for individuals who need help the most. This leads to better outcomes and a better experience for everyone involved.

Our high-performance networks are powered by more than 9,000 mobile doctors and nurses covering every county in the U.S., 3,500 healthcare providers and facilities in value-based arrangements, and hundreds of community-based organizations. Signifyâ€™s intelligent technology and decision-support services enable these resources to radically simplify care coordination for more than 1.5 million individuals each year while helping payers and providers more effectively implement value-based care programs

title: Data Analyst
description:
Job Description: Data Analyst (Ecommerce Marketing Agency)

Position Summary...

We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Data Analyst to join our ecommerce marketing agency. As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for managing and analyzing data for all of our ecommerce brands. Your primary focus will be to ensure the smooth operation of our data and attribution software, stitch together data from various sources, and provide valuable insights and recommendations based on data flow. The ideal candidate will have a strong analytical background, proficiency in data manipulation and visualization tools, and a deep understanding of ecommerce analytics.

Responsibilities:

Data Management and Integration:

â€¢ Gather, extract, and consolidate data from multiple sources, including website analytics, CRM systems, marketing platforms, and other relevant data repositories.

â€¢ Implement data integration processes to ensure accurate and consistent data across all ecommerce brands.

â€¢ Develop and maintain data pipelines and workflows to automate data collection and processing.

Data Analysis and Insights:

â€¢ Perform in-depth analysis of ecommerce data, including customer behavior, sales trends, campaign performance, and ROI.

â€¢ Identify key metrics and KPIs to track and monitor the success of marketing initiatives for each ecommerce brand.

â€¢ Provide actionable insights and recommendations to optimize marketing strategies, improve customer experience, and drive revenue growth.

â€¢ Conduct A/B testing and other statistical analyses to evaluate the effectiveness of marketing campaigns and initiatives.

Data and Attribution Software Management:

â€¢ Oversee the implementation and configuration of data and attribution software tools, ensuring smooth operation and accurate data tracking.

â€¢ Troubleshoot issues and discrepancies in data collection and reporting, working closely with the technical team to resolve any software-related problems.

â€¢ Stay updated on the latest advancements and best practices in data and attribution software, recommending changes or upgrades when necessary.

Reporting and Visualization:

â€¢ Create comprehensive and visually appealing reports and dashboards to present data insights and performance metrics to stakeholders.

â€¢ Develop standardized reporting templates and automate reporting processes to improve efficiency and scalability.

â€¢ Communicate findings and recommendations to internal teams, clients, and senior management in a clear and concise manner.

Collaboration and Consultation:

â€¢ Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including marketing, sales, and IT, to align data analytics initiatives with business goals and objectives.

â€¢ Advise on data-driven decision-making processes, ensuring the utilization of data analytics to drive business growth and competitive advantage.

â€¢ Assist in training and educating team members on data analytics tools, techniques, and best practices.

Qualifications and Skills:

â€¢ Proven experience as a Data Analyst, preferably in the ecommerce industry or a digital marketing agency.

â€¢ Strong proficiency in data manipulation and analysis using tools such as SQL, Python, R, or similar languages

This project involves analyzing industry trends and customer behavior in the tech sector...

title: Financial Data Analyst (Part-Time 1099 Contractor)
description:
Who we are - what we do
The Healthy Back Institute is on a mission to help people live pain free. Over the past 17 years, we have helped millions of people from around the world start thinking about health differently, to begin living pain-free, and most importantly in a safe and natural way. 
...
We accomplish this mission with our premium quality products and engaging content, while utilizing the awesome power of direct response marketing.

Freedom, Love, Team, Growth, Excellence, and Courage

These values form the foundation of how we serve our customers and how we treat each other.

We are seeking a highly talented Part-time Finance Data Analyst to join our team!

The Opportunity

As our Financial Data Analyst, you will be instrumental in unlocking HBI's future growth. You will be analyzing large sets of rich Financial Data, helping us identify trends, uncover hidden gems, and providing the insight and data to power intelligent decisions. You will be supporting various groups within the business, from marketing to finance, to operations as opportunities to utilize your high-level analytic skills arise.

This is a Part-Time Hourly Contractor, working 15-20 hours per month, reporting to the Fractional CFO, and you will be an important member of the Finance Team at HBI.

Who You Are

We are looking for a creative, seasoned analytical thinker who thrives on uncovering trends, discovering insights no one else has seen before, and presenting those findings in a clear, actionable format to the Executive Team. You love working with data to discover the solutions to tough business challenges. You are comfortable communicating with the executive team and want to help lead our organization into its next phase of growth.

This role will partner closely with the CFO to deliver and maintain monthly slide decks, data analysis and findings.

What You Have
3+ years as a Financial Data Analyst or similar analytics role with strong business acumen and experience in consulting, high-growth start-up or related business. Subscription-based company experience is a plus.
Highly proficient in Excel to manipulate large datasets.
Proficient in utilizing the company internal data warehouse.
Accurate interpretation of complex data sets, followed up by effective communication with the leadership team that both instills confidence, and motivates leadership to act on your recommendations.
Evidence of applying analytics skills and end-to-end quantitative thinking in order to optimize the performance of various business functions.
Ability to effectively communicate across matrixed organizations and explain technical concepts and data findings to business leaders.
Ability to manage tight, but reasonable, deadlines working with multiple stakeholders simultaneously.
Demonstrated high levels of ownership, entrepreneurial initiative, time management, organizational skills and a high desire to see your recommendations drive significant, measurable performance results for the business
What You'll Get To Do
Impact innovation in product, business model, pricing, and customer segment strategies.
Support CFO in monthly reporting utilizing the internal warehouse system, which includes department reports in channel and trend reporting.
Produce monthly slide decks and additional slides based on data findings.
Leverage complex data sets and analytics, including scenario and growth models, to recognize opportunities across the business and develop action plans to impact our finance efforts.
Conduct, analyze and maintain quantitative analysis on pricing, products, markets, customers and location to discover key business insights to support company performance and decisions.
Utilize considerable expertise and sound judgment in collaborating with the IT and Finance team in implementing research approaches to methodically manipulate, structure, extract, cleanse, sample, test and validate data from sources and significant volumes of complex data.
Provide guidance with data findings and partnership to business leaders and stakeholders on how best to harness available data in support of critical business needs and goals.

The People. You will be surrounded by some of the most talented, supportive, smart, and kind people, leaders, and teams - people you can be proud to work with.
The Mission. At HBI, we are relentlessly focused on helping people live pain-free lives. It feels good to serve others - and HBI is the leader in helping people live their lives pain-free.

This project involves analyzing industry trends and customer behavior in the tech sector...

title: Senior Data Analyst
description:
Bold Metrics is an AI-based platform that's transforming the apparel industry. Our platform helps retailers and brands reduce returns, improve sustainability, and optimize their supply chains. With machine learning and AI at our core, we're able to predict body measurements with incredible accuracy. This enables brands and retailers to better understand their customers' buying habits, the fit and... sizing of their products, and make optimizations in a completely new way. Our focus on data-driven insights is helping some of the world's most well-known brands and retailers leverage AI to impact their entire organization.

We are currently searching for a Data Analyst who wants to both dive deep into the data as well as get high-level and really think about what insights are meaningful to our clients. While working with a collaborative and energized team, you will have the opportunity to work with some of the biggest apparel brands and retailers in the world, come up with new ideas, and execute them to make a real impact. This is a full-time remote position.

About You:

You are a humble, passionate, and experienced data analyst that is excited to write code but also comfortable working with sales, accounts, and other engineers. You have a positive outlook and are interested in working in a highly collaborative work environment. If you have a natural curiosity for data and don't mind rolling up your sleeves and digging through messy data to find interesting insights, this might be your jam.

About the role:

As a Senior Data Analyst at Bold Metrics, you'll build reports that help retailers and internal teams understand our impact. You'll evaluate A/B tests, establish industry benchmarks, and uncover trends from shoppers worldwide. You'll need to bring new ideas, see the big picture, communicate with the team, and ensure projects are delivered on time. Your work will have a real impact on the industry and be seen by leaders at some of the top apparel brands and retailers in the world. You'll also develop and maintain metrics, reports, analyses, dashboards, and more, and translate data-related questions into persuasive analyses for business partners. You'll create compelling narratives and refine processes for data collection and analysis, among other responsibilities.

How you will make an impact:
â€¢ Youâ€™ll directly impact client relations with a full understanding of how weâ€™re able to impact their business
â€¢ Youâ€™ll work alongside our customer success team to help understand our client's needs and help answer and explore their data
â€¢ Youâ€™ll drive data analysis and help create analysis that the entire apparel industry will adopt

Skills and Qualifications : (even if you do not 100% meet these skills, we still welcome you to apply)
â€¢ 10+ years experience as a Data Analyst in a professional setting
â€¢ At least two years as a Senior Data Analyst
â€¢ Very comfortable with SQL & Python
â€¢ Able to identify trends and patterns in data
â€¢ 3+ years of experience with Tableau in a professional setting
â€¢ You can clearly communicate acceptance criteria and work well with a data team
â€¢ You love understanding the nuances of data and are excited to take command of client analysis and data
â€¢ Comfortable using a VPN, a database GUI and Jupyter
â€¢ Experience with DBT & Airflow is a plus
â€¢ Experience working on an eCommerce and/or retail site a plus
â€¢ B.A. or B.S. degree required

What We Offer:
â€¢ Competitive compensation
â€¢ Comprehensive health benefits, paid premium (medical, dental, vision)
â€¢ Flexible Paid time off and paid holidays
â€¢ Equity opportunities
â€¢ Ongoing paid training and growth opportunities

About Us:

Bold Metrics, founded in 2017, is a SaaS solution for retailers and brands to reduce returns, improve sustainability and supercharge their supply chain from the ground up. Using a comprehensive set of machine learning and A.I technologies to accurately predict customer body measurements, we help apparel brands unlock the power of body data to meet the demands of today's increasingly personalized world.

Learn more about us at boldmetrics.com

title: Statistician/Data Analyst
description:

Job Type...

Job Opening ID: 51691

Department: DOM General Internal Medicine

Bargaining Unit: 99

Job Location: UCI Campus- Irvine

Work Schedule: 8-5, M-F

Position Summary:

All of Us is a research program from the National Institutes of Health (NIH). It is seeking one million or more people from across the U.S. By doing so, it hopes to one day help speed up medical research. People who join will share information about their health, habits, and what it's like where they live. By looking for patterns, researchers may learn more about what affects people's health. The All of Us Research Program is building one of the largest biomedical data resources of its kind. The All of Us Research Hub stores health data from a diverse group of participants from across the United States.

Responsibilities will include study design, managing, cleaning, and analyzing a large number of data sets in varying formats, size, and origin, such as genomics data, data from electronic health records, user-generated data from health apps (including structured data such as usage logs and unstructured data such as online chatting transcripts), and datasets collected by the All of Us Research Program at UCI. The incumbent will be expected to interact with statisticians, data managers, and epidemiologists as well as other UCI team members, including faculty and staff researchers from several departments, and with the All of Us personnel, including programmers, program administrators, and others. The incumbent will be expected to work independently as well as under supervision, to provide support to data needs of all project teams as well as prepare analytical files, conduct statistical analyses, and prepare data and findings. The incumbent will prepare presentations as well as reports based on the data analyzed. The incumbent will also be expected to confer with data and IT personnel from other All of Us sites. Incumbent will also be expected to train staff members on the use of RedCap and other systems/platforms.

Total Compensation:

In addition to the salary range listed below, we offer a wealth of benefits to make working at UCI even more rewarding. These benefits may include medical insurance, sick and vacation time, retirement savings plans, and access to a number of discounts and perks. Please utilize the links listed here to learn more about our compensation practices and benefits .

Required:

â€¢ Minimum 5 years of experience in data science and biostatistics with preference in epidemiology, genetics, or population sciences setting
â€¢ Several years of programming and analyses experience working with R, SAS, REDCap, and Python
â€¢ Experience working with large data sets; experience with data from electronic health records and data collected from participants is required.

Master's or higher degree in statistics, data science, or biostatistics with strength in epidemiology, genetics, or population sciences.

Master's or higher degree in statistics, data science, or biostatistics with strength in epidemiology, genetics, or population sciences. Demonstrated ability to communicate both orally and in writing with researchers, programmers, and program administrators at all levels Demonstrated ability to resolve complex problems independently. Skilled in handling a large volume of project priorities, working on multiple tasks simultaneously, and shifting priorities as needed or directed. Ability to handle confidential materials in an appropriate manner. Ability to implement a variety of research data analytic mechanisms and reports; skill to analyze and organize information and provide comprehensive reports and presentations from data. Ability to clean up and merge large sets of complex data, and perform quality control

Knowledge of the health care system and other health related data. Knowledge of STATA is a plus.

title: Sr. IT Business Analyst

e. Stay current on emerging industry capabilities related to data management and business intelligence that could provide ongoing value to assigned business units.

f. Analyze and document requirements as well as current state reporting, business rules, and other variables relevant to building proposed data solutions.

g. Assist PTOs and developers building data solutions by clarifying business intelligence requirements and performing quality assurance (QA) testing of published data sets, ensuring accuracy and adherence to business rules.

h. Act as Data PTO when needed with support of Data Engineering Manager to support team workload. Provide leadership to less experienced team members on projects as well as user workgroups (centers of excellence).

i. Capture and maintain information for Data Inventory as well as metadata for published data sets.

k. Could also include researching how technology could be better leveraged by analyst team (e.g. Azure DevOps, SharePoint, etc.) and performing implementation tasks.

l. Assist Data Engineering Manager on objective to provide consistent, quality BI applications by developing templates, guidelines, and standards for the Data Analyst team to utilize.

m. Lead data stewardship processes, working with Data Owners, Stewards, and other stakeholders to recommend data sources, definitions, business rules, and data quality rules.

n. Facilitate discussions with management and staff in assigned business units to understand challenges and opportunities, which can be addressed with data solutions.

o. Develop and maintain knowledge of processes, objectives, systems, and data of assigned business units to pro-actively propose solutions and serve as SME on development efforts.

p. Mentor and train users in assigned business areas in use of BI tools, which enable them to access and analyze data efficiently to support their job functions and decision making.

q. Train and mentor less experienced analysts on relevant data technologies.

1. Required education:

College degree, preferably MIS, Mathematics, or another data-related degree. Equivalent experience will be considered.

2. Required experience:

6+ yearsâ€™ experience in role focused on data solutions such as Business Intelligence/Report development, Data Warehousing, or similar data focused initiatives. 2-4 yearsâ€™ experience as business systems analyst within software development lifecycles (for application development or data solutions).

3. Required skills:

Facilitation of requirements gathering and prioritization process as well as data stewardship efforts, working with both business unit and IT personnel. Ability to leverage BI technologies to provide end user access to data (report & dashboard building, semantic layer development, etc.). Strong analytical ability with attention to detail. Understanding of data structures, data analysis, and proficient with SQL. Must value operating in a collaborative and cooperative environment. Ability to show initiative, good judgment, and resourcefulness. Strong oral and written communication skills. Proficient with Microsoft Office tools.

title: Data Platform Systems Analyst
description:
Description

Your Job...

Koch Tax is seeking a Data Platform Systems Analyst to join our Data Management, Enablement and Transformation team, specifically to support our Data Platform Innovations Team. The ideal candidate for this role will need the ability to develop relationships, strong problem-solving skills to resolve and offer solutions in both functional and technical areas, and the ability to identify opportunities to advance and improve the product(s) and surrounding technologies. This candidate will leverage an innovative and collaborative mindset to partner with all levels of the organization to achieve a common goal.

Our Team

The DMET (Data Management, Enablement and Transformation) team is focused on developing a long-term sustainable capability utilizing data and technology to transform finance. This includes a diverse group with multiple teams focused on data platform technologies, specific data products and transformation. Our strategy will empower the finance and tax organizations to create superior value while consuming few resources, unlocking analytical capabilities, mitigating risk, and meeting ever-changing regulatory requirements.

What You Will Do
â€¢ Meet regularly with data product teams to understand requirements for platform architecture needs and translate requirements to technical team for delivery
â€¢ Facilitate communication when requirements need further clarification or adjustments due to technical constraints
â€¢ Conduct analysis to determine best path for solving business problems/opportunities
â€¢ Understand and document complex business processes and translate into technical requirements
â€¢ Assist in the design and testing of data products to ensure they meet business requirements
â€¢ Create and execute data validation and quality assurance
â€¢ Construct flow and decision diagrams to document business processes
â€¢ Act as liaison for the development teams to better communicate with data product teams, business users and more accurately define work and gather feedback
â€¢ Ensure that data products provide quality and accessible documentation to both technical and non-technical users
â€¢ Perform basic data analysis to validate and clarify data needs and requirements

Who You Are (Basic Qualifications)
â€¢ Understanding of the data development life cycle and data management principles (ETL/ELT process, SDLC (Software development lifecycle), metadata management, data quality, etc.)
â€¢ Ability to ask good questions to dig deep into processes; drive to truly understand product team needs and system issues
â€¢ Experience communicating and preparing visuals for users/stakeholders at various levels within an organization
â€¢ Experience working in Agile team, writing acceptance criteria that translate business need to technical requirements and vice versa

What Will Put You Ahead
â€¢ A deep curiosity and willingness to trace gaps in metadata (and ultimately quality) back to the originator to address and resolve issues proactively at the source
â€¢ Experience in understanding and correcting data discrepancies, identifying data anomalies, and root cause analysis
â€¢ Experience working in finance systems
â€¢ Experience with technologies such as AWS, Snowflake, Matillion, Alteryx, SQL, Tableau

At Koch companies, we are entrepreneurs. This means we openly challenge the status quo, find new ways to create value and get rewarded for our individual contributions. Any compensation range provided for a role is an estimate determined by available market data. The actual amount may be higher or lower than the range provided considering each candidateâ€™s knowledge, skills, abilities, and geographic location. If you have questions, please speak to your recruiter about the flexibility and detail of our compensation philosophy.

Hiring Philosophy

All Koch companies value diversity of thought, perspectives, aptitudes, experiences, and backgrounds. We are Military Ready and Second Chance employers. Learn more about our hiring philosophy here.

Who We Are

Koch Industries creates and innovates a wide spectrum of products and services that make life better. Our work spans a vast number of industries across the world, including engineered technology, refining, chemicals and polymers, pulp and paper, glass, electronics and many more. Headquartered in Wichita, Kansas, Koch employs 122,000+ employees across the globe.

At Koch, employees are empowered to do what they do best to make life better. Learn how our business philosophy helps employees unleash their potential while creating value for themselves and the company.

Our Benefits

Our goal is for each employee, and their families, to live fulfilling and healthy lives. We provide essential resources and support to build and maintain physical, financial, and emotional strength focusing on overall wellbeing so you can focus on what matters most. Our benefits plan includes medical, dental, vision, flexible spending and health savings accounts, life insurance, ADD, disability, retirement, paid vacation/time off, educational assistance, and may also include infertility assistance, paid parental leave and adoption assistance. Specific eligibility criteria is set by the applicable Summary Plan Description, policy or guideline and benefits may vary by geographic region. If you have questions on what benefits apply to you, please speak to your recruiter.

Equal Opportunities

Equal Opportunity Employer, including disability and protected veteran status. Except where prohibited by state law, all offers of employment are conditioned upon successfully passing a drug test. title: (USA) Analyst II, Systems Engineering
description:
Position Summary...

What you'll do...

Digital Media Services is the Walmart Global Tech team that engineers solutions and provides operational support for customer-facing and associate-facing digital experiences, including Digital-out-of-Home advertising, operational dashboards and the Walmart World Radio Network. We partner across the business with teams from Walmart US, Walmart Connect, Sam's Club and International BUs to design exciting and impactful digital experiences that drive revenue generation, positive customer sentiment and associate engagement.

This Analyst II, Systems Engineer position will be responsible for ensuring the reliable and efficient operation of a digital signage network. This will include tasks such as monitoring system performance, troubleshooting technical issues, and configuring software and hardware components. The ideal candidate should have a strong background in computer systems, networks, and software, as well as excellent communication and problem-solving skills.

What you'll do
â€¢ Monitor and support incidents related to the digital signage network.
â€¢ Troubleshoot technical issues that arise in the digital signage network, such as hardware or software malfunctions, network connectivity problems, and content display issues specifically related to BrightSign and MagicInfo.
â€¢ Configure and maintain the hardware and software components of the digital signage system, including media players, content management systems, and displays, with a focus on BrightSign and MagicInfo-specific configurations.
â€¢ Create and implement support programs for new projects/tests including writing support documentation, training technicians, and working with other teams to implement process changes.

What you'll bring
â€¢ Strong technical background in computer systems, networks, and software
â€¢ Knowledge of hardware and software components used in digital signage systems, such as media players, displays, and content management systems, with a focus on BrightSign and MagicInfo
â€¢ Experience in troubleshooting and resolving technical issues related to digital signage systems, specifically with BrightSign and MagicInfo platforms is a plus
â€¢ Solid knowledge of TCP/IP networking and experience working with network protocols, routing, and switching. Familiarity with VLANs, VPNs, and wireless networking protocols would be a plus.
â€¢ Knowledge of video encoding, transcoding, and streaming technologies such as H.264, MPEG-DASH, HLS, and RTSP/RTP
â€¢ Experience troubleshooting and identifying issues with HTML/JavaScript applications

About Walmart Global Tech
From entry-level to executive positions, Walmart provides limitless opportunities for growth, and career development. Walmart started small, with a single discount store and the simple philosophy of selling more for less. Today, we are a growing technology-enabled company founded on the same values as our first store. We establish clear expectations, empower associates to manage their work, and hold ourselves and one another to a high standard. Walmart's scale enables us to have an. No other company has the reach of Walmart, with 2.3 million associates worldwide and over 230 million weekly customers. Walmart is reshaping retail by investing in an expanding workforce. While technology is at the heart of our digital transformation, people are the reason we succeed and the force behind our innovations. We train our team in the skillsets of the future and bring in experts like you to help us grow.

Flexible, hybrid work
We use a hybrid way of working that is primarily virtual, while remaining near the locations Global Tech calls home. This approach helps us make quicker decisions, remove location barriers across our global team, be more flexible in our personal lives and spend less time commuting. Of course, being together in person is an important part of our culture and shared success. We use our campuses to collaborate and be together in person, as business needs require and for development and networking opportunities.

Benefits
Beyond our great compensation package, you can receive incentive awards for your performance. Other great perks include 401(k) match, stock purchase plan, paid maternity and parental leave, PTO, multiple health plans, and much more.

Equal Opportunity Employer
Walmart, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer - By Choice. We believe we are best equipped to help our associates, customers and the communities we serve live better when we really know them. That means understanding, respecting and valuing diversity- unique styles, experiences, identities, ideas and opinions - while being inclusive of all people.

The above information has been designed to indicate the general nature and level of work performed in the role. It is not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all responsibilities and qualifications required of employees assigned to this job. The full Job Description can be made available as part of the hiring process.

Minimum Qualifications...

Outlined below are the required minimum qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no minimum qualifications.

Option 1: Bachelor's degree in computer science, computer engineering, information systems, information technology, or related area.

Option 2: 3 years' experience in technology infrastructure engineering across areas such as compute, storage, network, mobility or virtualization relatedtechnologies.

Preferred Qualifications...

Outlined below are the optional preferred qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no preferred qualifications.

description:
As the Information Company, our mission at OpenText is to create software solutions and deliver services that redefine the future of digital. Be part of a winning team that leads the way in Enterprise Information Management.

â€¢ Experience in synthesizing SaaS analytics themes and key performance indicators â€“ storytelling with data

title: Data Scientist
description:
Imagine a workplace that encourages you to interpret, innovate and inspire. Job Description

Our Data Science team applies Advanced Analytics, Statistics, and Artificial Intelligence / Machine Learning to produce solutions that reduce customer health costs and improve outcomes and business processes.

Role Summary

Your work will require deep acquaintance with MultiPlanâ€™s data, seeking to find ways to deliver value through advanced feature engineering. As a data scientist part of a cross functional team you will work closely with Data & Engineering to deliver production ready code that is robust and ready to scale.

The ideal candidate for this role will have a deep understanding of data, probability and decision science while also having a passion for creating technology to improve health care with an attitude of creativity and continual learning.

Primary Responsibilities:

â€¢ Performs assessments and listens to internal/external customers to understand and anticipate their needs and determine their priorities in the context of the overall enterprise.
â€¢ Operate within established methodologies, procedures, and guidelines; work independently in a fast-paced, agile environment.

What we are looking for?
â€¢ Bachelorâ€™s or Masterâ€™s degree in Statistics, Operations Research, Applied Mathematics, Computer Science, Econometrics or similarly quantitative/technical field. Bachelorâ€™s or Masterâ€™s in a quantitative science or related field preferred!
â€¢ 3+ years of experience designing and developing statistically grounded decision modules.
â€¢ 3+ years of experience translating statistical models to functional code.
â€¢ 3+ years of experience in general programming language, e.g. Python or R. SQL experience preferred.
â€¢ 3+ years of experience in statistical computing and graphics.
â€¢ Knowledge of Git/GitHub integration with CI/CD tools.
â€¢ Problem solving, critical thinking, creativity, organizational, design, interpersonal, communication (written, verbal and listening) skills.
â€¢ Healthcare space experience is a PLUS!
â€¢ Process optimization experience desirable.

BENEFITS

We realize that our employees are instrumental to our success, and we reward them accordingly with very competitive compensation and benefits packages, an incentive bonus program, as well as recognition and awards programs. Our work environment is friendly and supportive, and we offer flexible schedules whenever possible, as well as a wide range of live and web-based professional development and educational programs to prepare you for advancement opportunities.

Life insurance

401(k) + match

Generous Paid Time Off
