title: Data Engineer
description:
Software Guidance & Assistance, Inc., (SGA), is searching for a Data Engineer for a FULL TIME assignment with one of our premier Technology clients in Fairfax, VA.

About the Role...
Our client is a market intelligence software company located in the Washington, D.C. area.
We have an existing commercial SaaS platform that consists of 3 components: a web application, several 3rd party databases integrated into our backend, and a Natural Language Processing, supervised ML model based on a custom taxonomy.

We are looking to build 2.0 of our platform, with a brand new front end based on new algorithms and an enhanced supervised deep learning model that uses a confluence of data from various data sources (e.g., patent, financial, and market data). It's a challenge and a fun opportunity for someone looking to make the next big platform that the world is going to use.

Our Data Engineer would have the opportunity to build strong Data and ETL infrastructure and practices to help enable this next generation of our machine learning. You will provide technical expertise and support in the design, development, implementation, and testing of 2.0. You will also participate in and/or direct major deliverables of projects through all aspects of the data lifecycle including the storage, processing and management of data; architecture and design; and building, managing and executing our ETL processes.

title: Data Analyst
description:
Description

The Data Analyst reports to the Director of Data Management and is an integral member of the Data Management Office. The Data Analyst plays a key role working with subject matter experts to ensure proper utilization of data via analysis, discovery and investigation of potential data quality issues. The Data Analyst will use his or her's skills in data analysis, data mapping, and... investigation to help business units and other associates in the data management group deliver key information assets like reports, data integrations, data quality profiles, dashboards and design documents. The data analyst will work on other data related projects as directed by the Manager of the Data Management Office.

Experience with data warehouse environments is highly desirable. Experience with SQL databases and business requirements gathering and creation will be necessary for this position. The Data Analyst will work closely with other team members of the Data Management Group which includes the Data Integration team, Business Intelligence, and Data Governance/Data Quality. The Data Analyst will communicate effectively with other team members and management to deliver results in a timely fashion.

The successful candidate for this role will have 5 or more years working in a similar capacity with excellent communication skills and hands on expertise with data query tools.

Responsibilities
â€¢ Work with management to prioritize data and information needs
â€¢ Working with subject matter experts and assisting the business analyst to translate needs to business requirements with an emphasis on non-technical, business friendly terms and language.
â€¢ Interpret data, analyze results
â€¢ Develop data mappings, data flows, and data lineage artifacts.
â€¢ Develop expertise in data structures, and data elements to assist other members of the Data Management Office.
â€¢ Identify and make recommendations as to acquisition of new sources of data.
â€¢ Identify data quality issues and make recommendations to improve the overall quality of data.
â€¢ Identify and define new process improvement opportunities

Education and Experience
â€¢ BA/BS in Business, computer science, Information Management or related discipline
â€¢ Proven working experience as a data analyst or business data analyst
â€¢ 5+ Years' professional experience

Required Skills
â€¢ Strong working knowledge writing queries in structured query language (SQL). Experience with other data manipulation and data preparation techniques and technologies
â€¢ Experience with one or more of the major database platforms (Oracle, MS Sql Server, MySql)
â€¢ Familiarity and working knowledge MS Office, Visio or other diagramming tools
â€¢ Excellent communication skills and the ability to articulate complex ideas and findings
â€¢ Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy
â€¢ Good working knowledge of data mapping techniques, and writing business requirements
â€¢ Experience and exposure to project management concepts and tools
â€¢ Required non-technical skills include: written communication, interpersonal skills working in an team environment, complex problem solving, results orientated, adaptability to change, self-motivated, able to see the big picture while delivering tangible results

title: Data Analyst III
description:
Position Summary...

What you'll do...

As a Data Analyst in our team, you will be responsible for all data related elements, including query building, developing data models, managing/creating KPIs and building impactful data visualizations. You will also have the opportunity to interact with businesses across different domains and to collaborate with multiple technical engineering teams.

About Team: Enterprise Business Services - Data Intelligence
Do you dream about data? Can you see patterns and answers in the data when others see just a bunch of numbers? Then, this role is for you! As a painter that uses raw colors to create a masterpiece, you will be the artist using raw, massive, and complex data sets to tell stories and create visualizations to uncover patterns, trends, and insights.

As part of the Enterprise Business Services - Data Intelligence team, you will be designing and developing analytical solutions with actionable insights across multiple areas and domains, helping the business in their analytical journey, unlocking savings, and supporting leadership in making better and faster decisions.

What you'll do:
â€¢ Develop metrics, storyboards, and dashboards by gathering data from various sources to tell a story about the data.
â€¢ Analyze complex data to identify patterns, detect anomalies in data using statistical concepts and tools.
â€¢ Use knowledge in Data Discovery tools to write queries and analyze data to identify patterns, trends, outliers, and correlations.
â€¢ Bring new ideas for data visualizations and analytics.
â€¢ Interact and work with multiple cross-functional teams.

What you'll bring:
â€¢ Hands-on experience in Visualization Tools like Power BI, Tableau, Looker, QlikView, SAP Lumira, MicroStrategy, etc.
â€¢ Develops and understand Data Model and define complex relationship within the tables.
â€¢ Demonstrates expertise in writing queries across large data sets.
â€¢ Expertise with RDBMS (Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL) with an excellent understanding of transaction management and performance tuning.
â€¢ Understanding of descriptive, predictive, and prescriptive analytics.
â€¢ Experience in scripting languages, such as, Python or R.
â€¢ Understand the conception of process mining, thru utilizing log data to build the process model.
â€¢ Ability on identifying process insights, gaps, and ROI opportunities.
â€¢ Be able to wireframe and mockup potential data visualization solutions to address the business requirements.
â€¢ Experience on working with Agile methodology - Kanban or SCRUM.
â€¢ Ability to work through ambiguity and drive for clarity of direction.
â€¢ Have previous experience in Celonis and being able to build basic PQL queries and PU-functions a plus.
â€¢ Have previous experience in Celonis, Celonis Studio, and Celonis Analysis visualizations and custom KPIs a plus.
â€¢ Develop interactive visualizations across multiple analyses with interactive, dynamic drilldown charts and OLAP tables with dynamic dimensions using user variables in Celonis a plus.
About Walmart Global Tech
Imagine working in an environment where one line of code can make life easier for hundreds of millions of people. That's what we do at Walmart Global Tech. We're a team of software engineers, data scientists, cybersecurity expert's and service professionals within the world's leading retailer who make an epic impact and are at the forefront of the next retail disruption. People are why we innovate, and people power our innovations. We are people-led and tech-empowered. We train our team in the skillsets of the future and bring in experts like you to help us grow. We have roles for those chasing their first opportunity as well as those looking for the opportunity that will define their career. Here, you can kickstart a great career in tech, gain new skills and experience for virtually every industry, or leverage your expertise to innovate at scale, impact millions and reimagine the future of retail.

Flexible, hybrid work:
We use a hybrid way of working that is primarily in office coupled with virtual when not onsite. Our campuses serve as a hub to enhance collaboration, bring us together for purpose and deliver on business needs. This approach helps us make quicker decisions, remove location barriers across our global team and be more flexible in our personal lives.

Benefits:
Benefits: Beyond our great compensation package, you can receive incentive awards for your performance. Other great perks include 401(k) match, stock purchase plan, paid maternity and parental leave, PTO, multiple health plans, and much more.

Equal Opportunity Employer:
Walmart, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer - By Choice. We believe we are best equipped to help our associates, customers and the communities we serve live better when we really know them. That means understanding, respecting and valuing diversity- unique styles, experiences, identities, ideas and opinions - while being inclusive of all people.

Outlined below are the required minimum qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no minimum qualifications.

Option 1: Bachelor's degree in Business, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, Analytics, Mathematics, Arts, Finance or related field and 1 year's
experience in data analysis, data science, statistics, or related field. Option 2: 3 years' experience in data analysis, data science, statistics, or related field

Data science, data analysis, statistics, or related field, Master's degree in Business, Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, Analytics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Information Technology or related field, Related industry experience (for example, retail, merchandising, healthcare, eCommerce), Successful completion of assessments in data analysis and Business Intelligence tools and scripting languages (for example, SQL, Python, Spark, Scala, R, Power BI, or Tableau)

description:
About Mynd:

Mynd is a tech-enabled real estate company serving the $85B+ property management and real estate investment market. Lead Data Governance Analyst

OPIS, a Dow Jones company, is one of the worldâ€™s most comprehensive sources for petroleum pricing and news information. Proven experience building a strong culture of governance

Technical capabilities to proactively improve processes and data quality

title: Senior Data Analyst - Celonis
description:
Position Summary...

What you'll do...

As a Data Analyst in our team, you will be responsible for all data related elements, including query building, developing data models, managing/creating KPIs and building impactful data visualizations. In additional, you will have the opportunity to interact with businesses across different domains and collaborate with multiple technical engineering teams.

About Team: Enterprise Business Services - Data Intelligence

Do you dream about data? Can you see patterns and answers in the data when others see just a bunch of numbers? Then, this role is for you! As a painter that uses raw colors to create a masterpiece, you will be the artist using raw, massive, and complex data sets to tell stories and create visualizations to uncover patterns, trends, and insights.

As part of the Enterprise Business Services - Data Intelligence team, you will be designing and developing analytical solutions with actionable insights across multiple areas and domains, helping the business in their analytical journey, unlocking savings, and supporting leadership in making better and faster decisions.

What you'll do:
â€¢ Develop metrics, storyboards, and dashboards by gathering data from various sources to tell a story about the data.
â€¢ Analyze complex data to identify patterns, detect anomalies in data using statistical concepts and tools.
â€¢ Use knowledge in Data Discovery tools to write queries and analyze data to identify patterns, trends, outliers, and correlations.
â€¢ Bring new ideas for data visualizations and analytics.
â€¢ Interact and work with multiple cross-functional teams.

What you'll bring:
â€¢ Hands-on experience in Visualization Tools like Power BI, Tableau, Looker, QlikView, SAP Lumira, MicroStrategy, etc.
â€¢ Have previous experience in Celonis.
â€¢ Develops and understand Data Model and define complex relationship within the tables.
â€¢ Demonstrates expertise in writing queries across large data sets.
â€¢ Expertise with RDBMS (Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL) with an excellent understanding of transaction management and performance tuning.
â€¢ Understanding of descriptive, predictive, and prescriptive analytics.
â€¢ Experience in scripting languages, such as, Python or R.
â€¢ Experience on gathering user requirements and leading design discussions for key insights.
â€¢ Evaluating and reviewing optimization opportunities in the defined PQL queries and data models.
â€¢ Mapping end-to-end process from the databases available to define the flow in Celonis.
â€¢ Monitoring and administering the EMS, identifying, and defining best practices for available extractors and data loads.
â€¢ Identifying opportunities for process improvement in conformance to the ideal state of the process flows.
â€¢ Experience on reviewing and interpret analyses in Celonis Studio with visualizations and custom KPIs.
â€¢ Develop interactive visualizations across multiple analyses with interactive, dynamic drilldown charts and OLAP tables with dynamic dimensions using user variables in Celonis.
â€¢ Good understanding of Celonis Analysis Settings and Permissions.
â€¢ Ability to work through ambiguity and drive for clarity of direction.
â€¢ Excellent verbal and written communications skills
â€¢ Experience on working with Agile methodology - Kanban or SCRUM.
â€¢ Ability to learn and adapt to new technologies, passion for continuous improvement.
â€¢ Experience leading projects working with large data sets, finding insights, and telling stories using data.
â€¢ Demonstrated high curiosity and ownership to learn and deep dive in problems.
â€¢ Demonstrated proficient in data mining principles: predictive analytics, mapping, collecting data from multiple data systems on premises and cloud-based data sources.
â€¢ Have knowledge on business process and SAP ERP Modules, such as, Account Payables, Finance (GL), Purchase Order, etc

About Walmart Global Tech
Imagine working in an environment where one line of code can make life easier for hundreds of millions of people and put a smile on their face. That's what we do at Walmart Global Tech. We're a team of 15,000+ software engineers, data scientists and service professionals within Walmart, the world's largest retailer, delivering innovations that improve how our customers shop and empower our 2.3 million associates. To others, innovation looks like an app, service, or some code, but Walmart has always been about people. People are why we innovate, and people power our innovations. Being human-led is our true disruption. We train our team in the skillsets of the future and bring in experts like you to help us grow. We have roles for those chasing their first opportunity as well as those looking for the opportunity that will define their career. Here, you can kickstart a great career in tech, gain new skills and experience for virtually every industry, or leverage your expertise to innovate at scale, impact millions and reimagine the future of retail.

Flexible, hybrid work
We use a hybrid way of working that is primarily virtual, while remaining near the locations Global Tech calls home. This approach helps us make quicker decisions, remove location barriers across our global team, be more flexible in our personal lives and spend less time commuting. Of course, being together in person is an important part of our culture and shared success. We use our campuses to collaborate and be together in person, as business needs require and for development and networking opportunities.

Benefits:
Beyond our great compensation package, you can receive incentive awards for your performance. Other great perks include 401(k) match, stock purchase plan, paid maternity and parental leave, PTO, multiple health plans, and much more.

Equal Opportunity Employer:
Walmart, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer - By Choice. We believe we are best equipped to help our associates, customers and the communities we serve live better when we really know them. That means understanding, respecting and valuing diversity- unique styles, experiences, identities, ideas and opinions - while being inclusive of all people.

Option 1: Bachelor's degree in Business, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, Analytics, Mathematics, Arts, Finance or related field and 2 years' experience in data analysis, data science, statistics, or related field. Option 2: Master's degree in Business, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, Analytics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Information Technology or related field. title: Data Center Power Delivery Project Manager
description:
About Us

At HDR, we specialize in engineering, architecture, environmental and construction services. While we are most well-known for adding beauty and structure to communities through high-performance buildings and smart infrastructure, we provide much more than that. We create an unshakable foundation for progress because our multidisciplinary teams also include scientists, economists... builders, analysts and artists. We believe that the way we work can add meaning and value to the world. That ideas inspire positive change. That coloring outside the lines can illuminate fresh perspectives. And that small details yield important realizations. Above all, we believe that collaboration is the best way forward.

HDR Engineering is looking for a Data Center (DC) Power Delivery Project Manager to join our growing local and nationally ranked team of Power Delivery professionals.

The primary duties of a DC PM include taking ownership of planning, scoping, and executing the Power Delivery engineering components of large data center and other mission critical facility projects and serving as the primary communication interface both internally to HDR teams and externally to the client.

Primary Responsibilities
â€¢ Establish themselves as the primary point of contact for the Power Delivery components of projects, with a key focus on establishing and implementing a robust, responsive communication approach and relationships, both internally and externally.
â€¢ Scope and proposal development, in Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) format, for data center substations interconnecting with electric utilities.
â€¢ Project team development and assignment, including technical leads by discipline, coordinating across the company for staff from multiple offices.
â€¢ Project management, including an understanding and application of basic project management tools and techniques, including project life cycle, client goals and objectives, contract terms and project risk, project scope/schedule/budget, project initiation, project planning, financial management and controls (including earned value), team management, change management, and project closeout.
â€¢ Communication liaison between the technical execution team and the client, including attending project meetings, performing regular client check-ins, and other duties to ensure communication breakdowns do not occur.
â€¢ Independently coordinates the work of engineers and the balance of the team throughout an entire project life cycle.
â€¢ Works independently and may direct, mentor, train, and/or supervise one or more Assistant PM's.
â€¢ Represents HDR to support marketing and proposal development for new opportunities.

Required Qualifications
â€¢ Bachelorâ€™s degree in Electrical or Civil/Structural Engineering, or similar combination of relevant education and experience preferred.
â€¢ 10 years of experience in engineering and/or project managing Power Delivery projects
â€¢ Basic technical knowledge of Power Delivery projects, including Substations, Transmission Lines, and/or Distribution systems preferred.
â€¢ Competence in Microsoft Word, Excel and Project
â€¢ Excellent communication and strong client and project management skills are required.
â€¢ Ability to thrive in a fast-paced and dynamic environment when rapid response is expected
â€¢ Knowledge of project scheduling and application in project delivery
â€¢ An attitude and commitment to being an active participant of our employee-owned culture is a must
â€¢ Position may require 25% or more travel at times

Preferred Qualifications
â€¢ Professional Engineer (P.E.) license or Engineer In Training (EIT) with active commitment to obtain P.E. preferred.
â€¢ Project Management Professional (PMP) or ability to obtain is desired.

Why HDR

At HDR, we know work isnâ€™t only about who you work for; itâ€™s also about what you do and how you do it. Led by the strength of our values and a culture shaped by employee ownership, we network with each other, build on each otherâ€™s contributions, and collaborate together to make great things possible. When you join HDR, we give you license to do the same. We help you take charge of your career, giving you multiple growth opportunities along the way.

We provide a comprehensive benefits package that promotes employee ownership, employee health, performance, and success, which includes medical, dental, vision, short and long-term disability, life insurance, an employee assistance program, paid time off, parental leave, paid holidays, 401(k) retirement savings plan with employer match, employee referral bonuses and tuition reimbursement. Overview

title: GIS Analyst/Data Manager
description:
USA Environmental, Inc. (USAE) is seeking a GIS Analyst/Data Manager for its Vieques, Puerto Rico office. This individual will be in charge of producing maps, managing GIS and tabular data, maintaining GPS equipment, and training personnel on various GPS equipment.

USAE will train the successful applicant in any additional skills needed for this position. The GIS Analyst/Data Manager will report... to the GIS Manager in USAE's FL Corporate office, but will take day to day assignments from the Site Manager in Vieques. Job Duties include but are not limited to: Edit and manipulate GIS data for map production and analysis.

Create maps for field teams, and project management. Become familiar with field data collection tablets, including use of ESRI's Survey123 data collection application. Perform quality control and corrections to project database.

Assist with data entry for daily field reports. Coordinate with contractor that maintains Vieques project database. Maintain GPS units used on site- including training field personnel on use and care.

Assist with administrative tasks when other employees are out of the office. When needed, assist with logistics shipping equipment or transporting goods and vehicles to and from the main island of Puerto Rico. Position Requirements are as follow: Degree in GIS, Geography, Earth/Environmental Science or related field with 1-3 years of experience.

GIS certificate or experience may substitute for degree requirements. Experience with ESRI ArcGIS software products (ArcMap, ArcCatalog, ArcToolBox. Knowledge of ArcGIS Online and data collection apps is a plus).

Strong database skills in both the GIS and Microsoft environment. Knowledge of Microsoft Excel. Knowledge of land survey techniques and Trimble GPS systems is a plus.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills. The ability to work with site management and field personnel. Excellent organization skills including data management.

Ability to speak Spanish is a plus. USAE is a small business that performs environmental remediation services for federal and non-Government clients. The company has 25 years of experience in providing Munitions and Explosives of Concern (MEC) characterization and remediation services, including unexploded ordnance (UXO) location, identification, removal & disposal.

USAE offers a comprehensive benefits and compensation package to include medical, dental, vision, life, and disability plans, matching 401(k) with 100% immediate vesting, and generous sick, vacation and holiday pay programs. In addition, USAE provides housing and per diem for meals and incidentals for non-local employees working in Vieques, as well as medical, dental, and vision plans. USAE also offers a one-time transportation stipend to be used to arrange for private transportation while on the island and provides regular home leaves to employees mobilized to the job site from the U.S.

and other locales. USA Environmental is an Equal Opportunity Employer - AA/M/F/Vets/Disabled

The United Nations Refugee Agency (UNHCR) is the worldâ€™s leading organization in helping and protecting the millions of people forced to flee their homes because of violence, conflict, and persecution. We deliver life-saving assistance, including shelter, food and water while also safeguarding fundamental human rights, safety, and dignity.

The Private Sector Partnerships Service (PSP) sits within UNHCRâ€™s Division of External Relations (DER) and is responsible for mobilizing resources and other forms of support from the private sector. UNHCR has developed a Private Sector Fundraising Strategy with the goal of raising $1 billion annually from the private sector. This strategy focuses on both Individual Giving (IG) and partnership and private philanthropy (PPH).

Individual Giving (IG) is targeted at the public to secure the support of individuals through regular, unrestricted donations, cash appeals and legacies. The aim is to generate both monthly and one-time donations from individuals using various channels and methods including direct mail, face-to-face fundraising, telemarketing, digital fundraising, DRTV and emergency fundraising, with focus on strong donor loyalty and lifetime value. Some markets in the Americas are currently using or creating regional or local instances of Salesforce as their main CRM, which will integrate with a global data warehouse, e-commerce, and automated marketing tools.

The Private Partnership and Philanthropy (PPH) section of PSP develops and strengthens long-term partnerships with companies, foundations, and high-net worth individuals. This includes leveraging the capacities of this segment to build long lasting partnerships that goes beyond resources but expands to
advocacy, communications, marketing, and public engagement.

Staff members are accountable to perform their duties as reflected in their job description.

Purpose and Scope of Assignment
The PSP Data Analysis Officer will support the regional fundraising strategy by leading and being responsible for the analysis of primary and secondary data for interpretation and informed decision making. The analyst will identify risks and opportunities based on insights derived from data from the region.

PSP Americas is looking to recruit an experienced analyst to support the regional PSP team and PSP markets in the Americas with advanced dashboarding, audience analysis, prospecting and fundraising reporting to support testing and optimization, increasing lifetime value, retention activities, budget decisions, marketing activity and, ultimately, fundraising income.

The post holder will collaborate closely with the PSP Regional Americas team, national fundraising markets (Canada, Mexico, Brazil), and National Fundraising Partners in Argentina and USA â€“ as well as with business insight and database experts in the region and at HQ, and with external vendors.

Weâ€™re looking for someone with experience in marketing who is passionate about drawing business insights. This role will support us in making informed marketing and budget decisions to support the delivery of UNHCR private sector fundraising, data strategy and data literacy across the Americas

Adherence to the values of UNHCR, and leadership to engage with fundraising experts is critical to meet the ambition of this position and to the delivery of the PSP Regional strategy.

title: Internal Auditor Data Analyst (FT)
description:
This role is responsible for both internal audit and data analytics activities. The role of Data Analyst and Internal Auditor will work as part of the Internal Audit team and split their time between performing internal audits and assisting in the development of advanced analytics and continuous monitoring within the Internal Audit department.

Within the capacity of an auditor, the individual... will participate in the execution of Internal Audit activities including evaluating risks, testing controls, and review processes related to the organization's internal controls, department procedures, and compliance with regulatory rules and company policies. They will assist with the tracking of open audit findings and facilitate response generation, information gathering, testing of evidence, and escalation of prior findings with Audit Management.

In addition, the position will also be responsible for implementing complex data analytics within the audit function. The role will be instrumental in the continued improvement of the internal control and governance processes via data analytics, reporting, and continuous monitoring activities.

Role Responsibilities
Perform internal risk assessments under the direction of Internal Audit Management.
Identify key controls, control design, and/or control deficiencies through the development of a risks and controls matrix.
Create process documentation, including process narratives and flow charts, to assist with audit planning and execution.
Create audit programs and testing procedures at the entity, process, transaction, or application levels.
Make recommendations on applying data analytics and continuous monitoring of audit activities during the audit process.
Assesses risks and internal controls by identifying areas of non-compliance; evaluating manual and automated processes; identifying process weaknesses and inefficiencies and technical issues.
Partner with internal clients to define action plans for deficiencies identified. Monitor completion of action plans and provide support when needed or requested by Audit Management.
Standardize and automate data preparation and reporting.
Collect, process, "clean", analyze, and report on data from various internal and external applications and databases as well as other data sources when necessary.
Identify and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets.
Train and develop data analytic skills within the Internal Audit team.
Evaluate accounting and/or technical documentation, previous reports, data, flowcharts, etc.
Create functional specifications and work closely with end-users to deliver business solutions.
Identify, define, and implement process automation and/or workflow improvements.
Perform other duties as assigned.

Role Requirements
Education
Bachelor's Degree in Business, Computer Science, Information Technology, Mathematics, or related field required.
Currently holds, or actively pursuing, an audit professional certification, such as CIA, CISSP, or CISA or equivalent audit credentials.
Required to hold an audit certification(s) as a condition of continued employment.
Professional certification(s) in data analytics preferred.
Experience
Three (3) years of experience in data analytics, audit, or an audit-related function such as accounting, risk management, IT, or other business or operational position required.
Advanced computer skills with various types of finance, accounting, database, and analytics technologies, such as Query SAP, Oracle, Enterprise Data Warehouses and/or Data Lakes, and other audit software and databases such as Highbond/Galvanize -ACL / Analytics Exchange, SQL, etc. required.
Experience with payment systems and financial services related to the credit/debit card industry preferred.
Knowledge, Skills, & Abilities
Solid understanding of financial services, systems, operational, and/or technology controls; knowledge of internal audit standards and practices; must have working knowledge of IT general controls
Knowledge of financial institution regulatory standards such as NCUA, OCC, FFIEC, Nacha ACH, or related a plus
Advanced analytical and scripting skills, including some experience with Python, SQL, MS Access, Server Management Studio, Cognos Query Editor, Jupyter Notebook, or Oracle cloud databases
Project a professional demeanor and can handle confidential matters with the utmost integrity
Ability to exercise discretion and good judgment in making decisions; strong problem-solving, reasoning, and analytical skills; high attention to detail
Project management and time-management skills, balancing multiple tasks and meeting deadlines
Strong Information Technology skills and working knowledge of SharePoint, a plus

The United Nations Refugee Agency (UNHCR) is the worldâ€™s leading organization in helping and protecting the millions of people forced to flee their homes because of violence, conflict, and persecution. We deliver life-saving assistance, including shelter, food and water while also safeguarding fundamental human rights, safety, and dignity.

The Private Sector Partnerships Service (PSP) sits within UNHCRâ€™s Division of External Relations (DER) and is responsible for mobilizing resources and other forms of support from the private sector. UNHCR has developed a Private Sector Fundraising Strategy with the goal of raising $1 billion annually from the private sector. This strategy focuses on both Individual Giving (IG) and partnership and private philanthropy (PPH).

Individual Giving (IG) is targeted at the public to secure the support of individuals through regular, unrestricted donations, cash appeals and legacies. The aim is to generate both monthly and one-time donations from individuals using various channels and methods including direct mail, face-to-face fundraising, telemarketing, digital fundraising, DRTV and emergency fundraising, with focus on strong donor loyalty and lifetime value. Some markets in the Americas are currently using or creating regional or local instances of Salesforce as their main CRM, which will integrate with a global data warehouse, e-commerce, and automated marketing tools.

The Private Partnership and Philanthropy (PPH) section of PSP develops and strengthens long-term partnerships with companies, foundations, and high-net worth individuals. This includes leveraging the capacities of this segment to build long lasting partnerships that goes beyond resources but expands to
advocacy, communications, marketing, and public engagement.

Staff members are accountable to perform their duties as reflected in their job description.

Purpose and Scope of Assignment
The PSP Data Analysis Officer will support the regional fundraising strategy by leading and being responsible for the analysis of primary and secondary data for interpretation and informed decision making. The analyst will identify risks and opportunities based on insights derived from data from the region.

PSP Americas is looking to recruit an experienced analyst to support the regional PSP team and PSP markets in the Americas with advanced dashboarding, audience analysis, prospecting and fundraising reporting to support testing and optimization, increasing lifetime value, retention activities, budget decisions, marketing activity and, ultimately, fundraising income.

The post holder will collaborate closely with the PSP Regional Americas team, national fundraising markets (Canada, Mexico, Brazil), and National Fundraising Partners in Argentina and USA â€“ as well as with business insight and database experts in the region and at HQ, and with external vendors.

Weâ€™re looking for someone with experience in marketing who is passionate about drawing business insights. This role will support us in making informed marketing and budget decisions to support the delivery of UNHCR private sector fundraising, data strategy and data literacy across the Americas

Adherence to the values of UNHCR, and leadership to engage with fundraising experts is critical to meet the ambition of this position and to the delivery of the PSP Regional strategy.

Duties and Responsibilities

â€¢ Support in the development of marketing dashboards for both regional and markets. Develop standard reports and benchmarking across markets and regions.
â€¢ Complete regular campaign analysis, gathering insights to inform fundraising strategies, identify areas of improvement and advice on targeting and prompting.
â€¢ Support the launch of new fundraising projects to ensure impact and response can be tracked effectively.
â€¢ Ensure that documentation is created for any new configuration, new reports set up and integration with third parties.

â€¢ Coordinate and enhance internal/external benchmarking and channel performance audits across Americas markets including Lifetime Value and other external benchmarking.
â€¢ Participate in market reviews, market entry and other strategy and analysis projects including PPH market, prospect and donor research as required.
â€¢ Run other reports and analysis as required.

â€¢ Provide training and support to fundraising practitioners on analysis, technical set up, data systems, building dashboards, reporting, and support capacity building as per market needs.

Data Strategy

â€¢ Support the creation and maintenance of market specific, channel specific reports and dashboards for ongoing reporting.

title: Data Analyst, PPM
description:
Job Description Overview

Today, SCA Health has grown to 11,000 teammates who care for 1 million patients each year and support physician specialists holistically in many aspects of patient care. Together, our teammates create value in specialty care by aligning physicians, health plans and health systems around a common goal: delivering on the quadruple aim of high-quality outcomes and a better... experience for patients and providers, all at a lower total cost of care.

As part of Optum, we participate in an integrated care delivery system that enables us to support our partners as they navigate a complex healthcare environment, Only SCA Health has a dynamic group of physician-driven, specialty care businesses that allows us to customize solutions, no matter the need or challenge:
â€¢ We connect patients to physicians in new and differentiated ways as part of Optum and with our new Specialty Management Solutions business.
â€¢ We have pioneered a physician-led, multi-site model of practice solutions that restores physician agency by aligning incentives to support growth and transition to value-based care.
â€¢ We lead the industry in value-based payment solutions through our Global 1 bundled payment convener, that provides easy predictable billing to patients.
â€¢ We help physicians address everything beyond surgical procedures, including anesthesia and ancillary service lines.

The new SCA Health represents who we are today and where we are goingâ€”and the growing career opportunities for YOU.
Responsibilities

We are seeking a highly motivated individual to assist in the development and execution of various types of monitoring and reporting to drive continuous improvement and efficiencies from the Project Management Office n(PMO). The Data Analyst is responsible for driving PMO health insights through reporting, metric tracking, and monitoring of Portfolio & Project Management data within the SCA Health systems and tools. This role will gather data from multiple sources and create reports, dashboards to illustrate the story the data tells. Your ability to take in requirements, obtain & interpret data, and return a meaningful illustration of it all will set you apart.

Working directly with PMO leadership you will drive the creative development of dashboards to illustrate key metrics from across the Project & Portfolio Management footprint. The position is also responsible for driving quality resource management data used in the ServiceNow tool for all Information Technology teammates. You will create dynamic reporting to assist leaders in decision making for resource usage, capacity planning, and teammate time tracking. Also assisting in driving the resource management tool usage and adoption. Additional duties include PMO internal metrics tracking and project management audits across the PMO.

This position requires proactiveness, willingness to learn from various business areas, and ability to make recommendations on how best to improve process and/or use technology to solve business problems.
Qualifications

Specific Job Skills
â€¢ Advanced Excel skills is a must - possessing the ability to use spreadsheets, graphing, tables, calculations, advanced formulas & functions, pivots, and automation efficiently to process large quantities of data relevant to business tasks.
â€¢ Strong experience with SQL development, databases, and reporting is a must.
â€¢ Exceptional analytical and organizational skills, including a proven ability to adapt to a dynamic project environment.
â€¢ Proven ability to manage key stakeholders while managing competing priorities.
â€¢ Strong leadership skills including conflict/issue resolution.
â€¢ Ability to communicate effectively both verbally and written with customers, stakeholders, and senior leadership.
â€¢ Ability to work effectively with project resources across multiple departments.
â€¢ Substantial experience and working knowledge of Microsoft Office, Teams, SharePoint (Microsoft Office 365 experience is a must. Azure is a plus)
â€¢ Strong experience with SQL development, databases, and reporting is a must.
â€¢ Knowledge and usage of Excel Power Pivot
â€¢ Knowledge of Power B.I. is a plus

title: Staff Data Analyst - People Analytics Product Manager
description:
Position Summary...

What you'll do...

About the Team/Position

One word: Impact

Our 2.2 million associates truly make the difference. The Associate Analytics team empowers our associates around the world to do more for our customers by improving people decisions through science, insight, and automation. We influence Walmart's people policies; test & evaluate program and intervention effectiveness; create scaled AI/ML people solutions; and deliver insights that improve our associates' experience. Our team has recently expanded scope so we're looking to grow quicklycome build with us!

The Senior Manager, Product Management is responsible for leading all product management activities for multiple Associate Analytics', Scaled BI products with an end goal of empowering our customers to make the best possible, data driven decisions for their business. The Product Manager should be an intense customer advocate who expertly captures the voice of our customer throughout the product life cycle. They should also be an influential consultant with experience in both the people/human resources function as well as building analytics products/capabilities. Lastly, the Product Manager will closely partner with our Data Stewardship and Business Intelligence teams - often leading agile ceremonies and overseeing the scrum, iterative development process end-to-end.

You'll sweep us off our feet if...
â€¢ You have experience in People Analytics product management and/or consulting capacity with a strong passion in improving overall employee/associate experience through Scaled BI Solutions.
â€¢ You are adept in requirements scoping, uncovering the pain points of customers, translating into business requirements for products and solutions that provide the best, most insightful solution, or experience for our customers.
â€¢ You have experience driving change management and solution adoption across multiple personas and products through push/pull communication channels and other change management techniques.
â€¢ You have experience implementing scaled customer listening mechanisms for established and new products with a goal of leveraging feedback to build prioritized product backlogs.
â€¢ You should be comfortable influencing senior leaders and business stakeholders while also building strong relationships across the functional and technology teams.
â€¢ You are comfortable leading agile ceremonies and partnering with teams to successfully execute throughout the product development cycle.

You'll make an impact by...

Data Source Identification: Supporting the understanding of the priority order of requirements and service level agreements. Helping identify the most suitable source for data that is fit for purpose. Performing initial data quality checks on extracted data.

Data Strategy: Understanding, articulating, and applying principles of the defined strategy to routine business problems that involve a single function.

Understanding Business Context: Requires knowledge of Industry and environmental factors; Common business vernacular; Business practices across two or more domains such as product, finance, marketing, sales, technology, business systems, and human resources and in-depth knowledge of related practices; Directly relevant business metrics and business areas. To Provide recommendations to business stakeholders to solve complex business issues. Develop business cases for projects with a projected return on investment or cost savings. Translate business requirements into projects, activities, and tasks and aligns to overall business strategy and develops domain specific artifact. Serve as an interpreter and conduit to connect business needs with tangible solutions and results. Identify and recommend relevant business insights pertaining to their area of work.

Tech. Problem Formulation: Requires knowledge of Analytics/big data analytics / automation techniques and methods; Business understanding; Precedence and use cases; Business requirements and insights. To translate/ co-own business problems within one's discipline to data related or mathematical solutions. Identify appropriate methods/tools to be leveraged to provide a solution for the problem. Share use cases and gives examples to demonstrate how the method would solve the business problem.

Data Visualization: Generating appropriate graphical representations of data and model outcomes. Understanding customer requirements to design appropriate data representation for multiple data sets. Working with User Experience designers and User Interface engineers as required to build front end applications. Presenting to and influencing the team and business audience using the appropriate frameworks and conveys clear messages through business and stakeholder understanding. Customizing communication style based on stakeholder under guidance and leverages rational arguments. Guiding and mentoring junior associates on story types, structures, and techniques based on context.
â€¢ Demonstrating up-to-date expertise and applies this to the development, execution, and improvement of action plans by providing expert advice and guidance to others in the application of information and best practices; supporting and aligning efforts to meet customer and business needs; and building commitment for perspectives and rationales.
â€¢ Providing and supporting the implementation of business solutions by building relationships and partnerships with key stakeholders; identifying business needs; determining and carrying out necessary processes and practices; monitoring progress and results; recognizing and capitalizing on improvement opportunities; and adapting to competing demands, organizational changes, and new responsibilities.
â€¢ Modeling compliance with company policies and procedures and supports company mission, values, and standards of ethics and integrity by incorporating these into the development and implementation of business plans; using the Open Door Policy; and demonstrating and assisting others with how to apply these in executing business processes and practices.

The above information has been designed to indicate the general nature and level of work performed in the role. It is not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities and qualifications required of employees assigned to this job. The full Job Description can be made available as part of the hiring process.

At Walmart, we offer competitive pay as well as performance-based incentive awards and other great benefits for a happier mind, body, and wallet. Health benefits include medical, vision and dental coverage. Financial benefits include 401(k), stock purchase and company-paid life insurance. Paid time off benefits include PTO (including sick leave), parental leave, family care leave, bereavement, jury duty and voting. Other benefits include short-term and long-term disability, education assistance with college degrees, company discounts, military service pay, adoption expense reimbursement, and more.

Eligibility requirements apply to some benefits and may depend on your job classification and length of employment. Benefits are subject to change and may be subject to a specific plan or program terms. For information about benefits and eligibility, see One.Walmart.com/Health

That means understanding, respecting and valuing diversity- unique styles, experiences, identities, ideas and opinions - while being inclusive of all people.

description:
Aeyon is committed to Integrity, Service, Excellence, and Innovation - Always!

Your day-to-day work will include the following:

Aeyon is currently seeking qualified candidates to support the Department of Navy's (DON) Financial Management Transformation Initiatives Audit Remediation effort in the execution of the following programs: Data Cleansing

This position will require candidates to apply technical expertise and skills to implement business solutions. Level III Data Analysts provide direction to project teams and interact with FM&C and Government clients at the Branch and Division Head Levels.

Responsibilities include but are not limited to the following:
â€¢ Prepare and remediate financial data for migration to Navy ERP to include an end-to-end data assessment.
â€¢ Analyze and define the scope of data identifying data quality and problem conditions.
â€¢ Develop and deploy scheduling tools that will improve efficiency in analyzing, reporting, and presenting the information.
â€¢ Recommend KPIs and metrics to facilitate continuing evaluations of data health, quality, and migration readiness milestones of all BSO activities scheduled for Navy ERP go-lives.
â€¢ Develop a comprehensive strategy to decrease or eliminate abnormal conditions for Navy commands before they migrate to NERP.

â€¢ Perform end-to-end data mapping of data to be migrated to NERP and mock conversions.
â€¢ Test and validate mock data conversions. Identify performance measures, metrics, and KPIs relevant to the mock master and transactional data loads that support the pre-migration conversion testing process and schedule.
â€¢ Provide KSDs to support external reviews of data cleansing actions and decisions for the accounting treatment of individual records.

Six (6) years of progressive, relevant experience. Ideal candidates will have experience supporting IT Development (SDLC - Technical documentation, requirements, design, testing, change management or deployment) or creating/maintaining databases or data and analytics experience (creation of data visualizations, analytic data reports, data cleansing scripts, and processes or performing technical data analytics) for State or Federal Government agencies or large, complex companies (greater than 1,000) employees.

Remote

title: Sr. IT Business Analyst
description:
GDH had partnered with an enterprise company that is actively looking for a Sr. IT Business Analyst. You will be responsible for pulling value from data by working with assigned business units to understand opportunities where data solutions can support business objectives, improve process efficiency, or support data driven decision making. To deliver on these opportunities, the Senior IT... Business Data Analyst analyzes business requirements and associated data, and provides subject matter expertise on systems, data, and business processes to teams tasked with building data solutions. To mitigate risks associated with data usage, the Senior IT Business Data Analyst facilitates data and BI stewardship to ensure data is used consistently and accurately throughout the organization, leading to confident decisions based on trusted data. Additionally, Senior IT Business Data Analysts develop BI data models as well as BI applications (e.g. reports, dashboards, data visualizations) to enable valuable usage of data assets. As a senior member of the Data Analyst team, the Senior IT Business Data Analyst assists the Data Engineering Manager in development of new processes, templates, and mentoring of less experienced analysts.
Responsibilities:

a. Develop, enhance, and support BI models and applications (e.g., reports, dashboards, data visualizations) in support of customer needs in assigned business areas.

b. Partner with assigned business areas to ensure that BI applications and workspaces are optimized for business purpose and aligned with relevant data governance policies.

c. Gather and forward customer feedback and suggestions for product improvement.

a. Resolve BI issues utilizing excellent customer service, problem solving, and technical thinking/reasoning skills following established support process and metrics guidelines.

b. Measure and analyze incoming issues to determine root cause and develop technical and training solutions to minimize reoccurrences and severity; report results to management.

c. Accurately document all customer issues, resolution steps, and gather feedback in support tracking software to enhance identifying and reporting trends leading to recurring problems.

d. Develop and publish support documentation for internal users for troubleshooting, training and other areas as needed.

e. Primary BI technology stack in use is Microsoft, which includes SSAS, SSRS, Power BI, and Excel BI components. Other technologies could be required due to changing business or technical needs.

d. Reach and maintain proficiency in all technologies relevant to position. Learn new features as they become available in technology stack utilized by Data Analyst team,

e. Stay current on emerging industry capabilities related to data management and business intelligence that could provide ongoing value to assigned business units.

f. Analyze and document requirements as well as current state reporting, business rules, and other variables relevant to building proposed data solutions.

g. Assist PTOs and developers building data solutions by clarifying business intelligence requirements and performing quality assurance (QA) testing of published data sets, ensuring accuracy and adherence to business rules.

h. Act as Data PTO when needed with support of Data Engineering Manager to support team workload. Provide leadership to less experienced team members on projects as well as user workgroups (centers of excellence).

i. Capture and maintain information for Data Inventory as well as metadata for published data sets.

j. Assist the team with the design processes and develop supporting materials such as document templates to assist Data Analyst team in effective support of the companyâ€™s data strategy.

k. Could also include researching how technology could be better leveraged by analyst team (e.g. Azure DevOps, SharePoint, etc.) and performing implementation tasks.

l. Assist Data Engineering Manager on objective to provide consistent, quality BI applications by developing templates, guidelines, and standards for the Data Analyst team to utilize.

m. Lead data stewardship processes, working with Data Owners, Stewards, and other stakeholders to recommend data sources, definitions, business rules, and data quality rules.

n. Facilitate discussions with management and staff in assigned business units to understand challenges and opportunities, which can be addressed with data solutions.

o. Develop and maintain knowledge of processes, objectives, systems, and data of assigned business units to pro-actively propose solutions and serve as SME on development efforts.

p. Mentor and train users in assigned business areas in use of BI tools, which enable them to access and analyze data efficiently to support their job functions and decision making.

q. Train and mentor less experienced analysts on relevant data technologies.

1. Required education:

College degree, preferably MIS, Mathematics, or another data-related degree. Equivalent experience will be considered.

2. Required experience:

6+ yearsâ€™ experience in role focused on data solutions such as Business Intelligence/Report development, Data Warehousing, or similar data focused initiatives. 2-4 yearsâ€™ experience as business systems analyst within software development lifecycles (for application development or data solutions).

3. Required skills:

Facilitation of requirements gathering and prioritization process as well as data stewardship efforts, working with both business unit and IT personnel. Ability to leverage BI technologies to provide end user access to data (report & dashboard building, semantic layer development, etc.). Strong analytical ability with attention to detail. Understanding of data structures, data analysis, and proficient with SQL. Must value operating in a collaborative and cooperative environment. Ability to show initiative, good judgment, and resourcefulness. Strong oral and written communication skills. Proficient with Microsoft Office tools.

Job Description

NRELâ€™s Strategic Energy Analysis Center is seeking an undergraduate intern to perform data analysis tasks related to the potential impacts of the Inflation Reduction Act (IRA). The IRA introduced a wide range of customer and commercial incentives that are expected to meaningfully shift the U.S. energy mix. Customer incentives, in particular, are expected to drive a transition where energy demand in the U.S. buildings and transportation sectors will increasingly be met by electricity, with corresponding reductions in natural gas and gasoline consumption.

We are seeking an undergraduate intern to assist with data analysis that will provide initial insights into this shift by quantifying the potential changes in demand and consumer expenditures by fuel type. If time and budget allow, the candidate may also explore how the potential impacts vary by region and customer demographics.

Basic Qualifications

â€¢ Interest in interdisciplinary analysis related to energy supply and demand

title: Data Analyst

description:

Only Serious Applicants Please And Should Have A Substantial Experience Working In Real Estate/Hospitality Industry, Luxury Hotels And Apartments and the likes...

Here is what is expected of the analysis:

1. Get the map of our four cities of operation, and prepare a detailed price map for each of them.

2. The price map must contact the zip code of each of the location, address, and average price for that location.

title: Customer Data Analyst
description:
Every day, Global Payments makes it possible for millions of people to move money between buyers and sellers using our payments solutions for credit, debit, prepaid and merchant services. Our worldwide team helps over 3 million companies, more than 1,300 financial institutions and over 600 million cardholders grow with confidence and achieve amazing results. Join our dynamic team and make your mark on the payments technology landscape of tomorrow.

Summary:

The Customer Insights team provides Global Payments' International Sales Regions and Software Vertical Markets with insights into their business performance utilizing Customer Experience (CX) strategies via survey campaigns driven by Medallia. The Customer Insights team takes that data and provides Sales and Operations feedback aimed at driving literal Client Success, supporting our company's goal to provide a best in class experience to our clients, and stay on the pulse of what our clients are facing due to macroeconomic forces in the economy versus how our pricing and products support them.

The Customer Data Analyst acts as a storyteller for the data we receive from our customers. We combine data from multiple sources and need to be interpreted in a way that drives actionable insights for our stakeholders. Be responsible for data analysis and data sets related to all customer experience activities within the organization

Collect, analyze and create reports for key commercial business reviews and for tracking customer experience performance. This is done by using impactful dashboards and effective visualizations that provide actionable information to allow the business to draw conclusions and devise action

Assisting our other analysts in building reports for qualitative and quantitative research

Building reports for our Vertical Markets in Medallia Admin Suite

You will be successful in this role if you:

An organized, energetic, self starter who loves to run with an idea and add their own take while pursuing the team and company goal.

Intellectually curious - seeks out data that is the foundation of a storyline, and then are adept at building and telling that story

Appreciates telling the story for our customers through the data and analytics we have

Proficiency in querying, joining, and manipulating raw datasets for analysis

Experience with building reports and dashboards

Familiar with pulling exports from various CRM platforms

Comfortable with compiling data from multiple sources to drive actionable insights

Someone who loves utilizing technology to deliver results

Experience in business analytical writing or storytelling with data

Proficient in Google Sheets or Excel. Knowledge of data analytic formulas a plus

Bachelor's degree in Science, Technology, Mathematics, Business Administration, Economics, or in a STEM related degree preferred

Prefer this role to be based in Jeffersonville Indiana, or Lindon Utah, but open to remote for the right candidate. May require travel - approximately 5% domestically at most

title: Colorado Aquatic Data Specialist
description:

Colorado Aquatic Data Specialist

Job Code: 2023-AIM-006

Location: Lakewood

State: Colorado

Program: Assessment Inventory Monitoring

Contract Length: Over 12 Months

Job Description

The Great Basin Institute (GBI) partnerâ€™s with the Bureau of Land Management (BLM) throughout the western United States to implement vegetation monitoring programs such as the Assessment, Inventory, and Monitoring (AIM) program. The AIM program is a BLM initiative to collect field data on rangeland indicators characterizing soil, vegetation, and hydrologic resources with an overarching goal to inform land management decisions and conservation actions.

The Bureau of Land Management (BLM) manages approximately 3,000 miles of perennial streams, as well as thousands of miles of intermittent and ephemeral streams within the state of Colorado. The BLM is mandated to conduct land health monitoring to document effectiveness of the decisions established in its Resource Management Plans and meet guidance in FLPMA, to determine treatment effectiveness, BMP effectiveness, or compliance with applicable laws and regulations, etc.

GBI seeks to fill a Data Specialist for data management, processing, and analysis in support of Lotic AIM data collection in Colorado from July 2023 through September 2024 (total 14 months). The data specialist is required to have a thorough and comprehensive understanding of lotic AIM data collection and data management protocols to enable rigorous data review procedures. The Colorado Data Specialist will work at the BLM Colorado State Office, but can be physically located at another BLM office within the State to assist BLM staff with review and completion of Quality Assurance (QA) / Quality Control (QC) procedures for AIM datasets, provide technical support and training to field staff in the use of ArcGIS Field Maps and Survey123, work with BLM staff on data management and storage issues for AIM and related datasets, and complete basic analysis and reporting using AIM data as needed for completion of BLM business. The position also requires coordination with BLM district project leads in developing design management spreadsheets for the FY23 field season.

Specific Tasks May Include The Following

The data specialist will work directly with BLM staff on a daily basis, and will coordinate with the state lotic AIM lead and monitoring coordinator for identification and completion of day-to-day tasks. Although the position is intended to be run out of the BLM Colorado State Office, remote work is possible. Additional travel may be required to support field crews, and for workshops on incorporating AIM data into land health evaluations.
â€¢ Assist BLM field monitoring crews collecting AIM data with mid-season data quality and completeness checks;
â€¢ Assist BLM Colorado State Office staff in conducting data quality reviews as AIM data are collected throughout the field season;
â€¢ Independently perform quality control checks on the data, organize it in a standardized way as coordinated with the BLM state office staff, and assist in submitting the data to BLMâ€™s national operations center for ingestion to AquaDat;
â€¢ Periodically retrieve data from AquaDat, state water quality databases, complete basic analysis tasks, and requested reports or summaries;
â€¢ Analyses and reports may include aggregation of data provided in two or more databases, summaries of indicator calculations for a given project area, including estimates of variance, comparisons of indicator values by stratum, and production of basic maps using ArcMap (ESRI);
â€¢ Creation of create standard summary templates or tools for field/district offices in CO, such as a standard summary table to be used for land health assessments, biological assessments, and NEPA;
â€¢ Train at one Lotic AIM training within Colorado or closest neighboring state;
â€¢ Assist BLM Colorado Project Leads with post-training calibration requiring travel for two (2) days

and one (1) night;
â€¢ Camp overnight with AIM field crews stationed at these locations for up to three (3) days and two (2) nights to assist with data collection as needed;
â€¢ During the field season, be available to provide technical support to field staff regarding data entry and management, particularly with regards to Survey123 and Field Maps;
â€¢ Ability to complete occasional field work; and
â€¢ Must be able to pass a federal background clearance and complete all required security trainings (FISSA) needed for federal building and computer network access.

Contract Timeline

This is a 14 month term with the potential of additional funding that would extend the term. The ideal start date is July 10th, 2023. Start date is flexible, please contact GBI if you have any questions regarding project timeline.

Location:

The position is based in Lakewood, CO at the BLM Colorado State Office; however, location is flexible with hybrid remote working options available.

Compensation And Benefits
â€¢ Pay Rate: $25.00 - $26.50 per hour depending on experience.
â€¢ Health, Dental, and Vision Insurance paid 100% by GBI. Available first day of month following first day of employment. For more details on each benefit plan, please contact hr@gbinstitute.org.
â€¢ Paid Leave Benefit: Vacation accrued at 4 hours per 80 hour pay period starting on first day of employment. Sick Leave accumulated at 4 hours per pay period starting on first day of employment with a maximum of 40 hours earned and used within the award period of July 1 and June 30 annually.
â€¢ Eligible to enroll in GBI 401K Employer Plan on the first of the month following 90 days of employment. GBI will match up to 4% of employeeâ€™s contribution.

Education

Job Qualifications:
â€¢ Bachelorâ€™s degree in aquatic hydrology/ecology or related natural resources field

Experience
â€¢ Minimum 2 years specialized experience or related graduate work, including experience with running r-scripts, python and/or other programming languages, Shiny, ESRI tools, and managing large datasets;
â€¢ Field experience in fisheries, hydrology, fluvial geomorphology, water quality sampling, including previous Lotic AIM monitoring experience;
â€¢ Proficiency with ESRI products (e.g., ArcMap, web maps) and basic statistical packages and clearly instruct others in technical material;
â€¢ Ability to work with multiple field and district office leads in complex work environments, interest and ability to learn and grow professional skills; and

title: Sr. IT Business Analyst

m. Lead data stewardship processes, working with Data Owners, Stewards, and other stakeholders to recommend data sources, definitions, business rules, and data quality rules.

o. Develop and maintain knowledge of processes, objectives, systems, and data of assigned business units to pro-actively propose solutions and serve as SME on development efforts.

1. Required education:

College degree, preferably MIS, Mathematics, or another data-related degree. Equivalent experience will be considered.

2. Required experience:

6+ yearsâ€™ experience in role focused on data solutions such as Business Intelligence/Report development, Data Warehousing, or similar data focused initiatives. 2-4 yearsâ€™ experience as business systems analyst within software development lifecycles (for application development or data solutions).

3. Required skills:

Facilitation of requirements gathering and prioritization process as well as data stewardship efforts, working with both business unit and IT personnel. Ability to leverage BI technologies to provide end user access to data (report & dashboard building, semantic layer development, etc.). Strong analytical ability with attention to detail. Understanding of data structures, data analysis, and proficient with SQL. Must value operating in a collaborative and cooperative environment. Ability to show initiative, good judgment, and resourcefulness. Strong oral and written communication skills. Proficient with Microsoft Office tools.

â€¢ Experience with NNSA Defense Programs areas of responsibilities

title: Telemetry Data Analyst
description:
Telemetry Data Analyst - Part Time Needed

Integrated Statistics is looking for a part-time Telemetry Data Analyst to support the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) National Marine Fisheries Service (NMFS) Northeast Fisheries Science Center (NEFSC...

The Telemetry Data Analyst will work with the Seal Ecology and Assessment Program within the Protected Species Branch. The mission of the Seal Program is to provide scientific information to managers and stakeholders on the role of seals as important sentinels of the marine ecosystem, support conservation efforts to maintain a healthy and optimally stable population of seals in the northeast, and provide recommendations on mitigation measures to minimize conflicts between seals and humans. As part of this program we study the abundance of stocks in the Northwest Atlantic via manned and unmanned surveys to investigate population trends and distribution, as well as behaviors of individual seals via acoustic and satellite telemetry to investigate how behavior may be influenced by ecological and anthropogenic factors.

The Telemetry Data Analyst will work with others in the Seal Program to analyze pinniped telemetry data. Duties include summarizing telemetry tracks, dive behaviors, and acoustic detections from tagged individuals; fitting appropriate models to these data to evaluate movements, occurrence, or foraging behavior of tagged individuals; building species distribution models from existing telemetry and sightings data to evaluate overlap with anthropogenic activities; assisting in grant report writing; and publishing findings in peer-reviewed manuscripts. Qualifications
â€¢ Graduate degree or equivalent in fisheries, quantitative ecology, or a closely related field - required
â€¢ Experience processing and interpreting ARGOS/Wildlife Computer satellite telemetry data - required
â€¢ Demonstrated proficiency in R to process and analyze telemetry data - required
â€¢ Excellent communication skills both verbally and using
written materials (including visual presentations) with a variety of
audiences including technical, scientific, and the general public - required
â€¢ US citizenship and presence, and the ability to comply with EO 14042 - required
â€¢ Experience utilizing state-space models or equivalent to model and predict animal movements and behaviors through time - preferred
â€¢ Experience with Oracle tables and SQL language - preferred

The position is part-time, with some flexibility in hours. The rate of
pay depends on skills and experience. The work may potentially be performed remotely. The position is for one year, with
the possibility of extension.

Integrated Statistics is an equal opportunity employer and will not discriminate against any employee or applicant on the basis of age, color, disability, gender, national origin, race, religion, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran status, or any classification protected by federal, state, or local law. title: International Trade Data Analyst
description:
Job Description - International Trade Data Analyst (2300007D)

International Trade Data Analyst...

Firm Summary
White & Case is an elite global law firm serving leading companies, financial institutions and governments worldwide. Our long history as an international firm means we are perfectly placed to help our clients resolve their most complex legal challenges wherever they may be. With lawyers operating from more than 40 locations, working in virtually every country of the world, we have invested heavily in building a high-quality full-service practice competing at the top of the market. We are distinguished by our on-the-ground presence in the world's key financial markets and our strengths in handling complex cross-border work. It's not just about our global network of offices; it's the global interconnectedness of the Firm that our people, and our clients, value most. We work well together across geographic and practice boundaries. It's one of the reasons we attract and retain cross-border work. And why we attract a diverse group of people. Our lawyers are globally minded, enterprising, collaborative and committed to excellence. Diversity is a core value of our Firm and it has been recognized with numerous awards and top rankings around the world. Our people represent 90 nationalities and speak 80 languages.

Our Practice Area
White & Case employs over 2000 lawyers and more than 200 legal assistants located in 38 offices around the world. We thrive on innovation and diversity and the benefits that such qualities afford our clients and ourselves. Clients choose to work with us because we have unparalleled expertise and passion to solve the complex issues that affect the success or the very survival of their organizations. Our open door policy promotes candid communication among partners, associates, legal assistants and staff. We attract dynamic people with formidable talents and we encourage them to be both generous with their knowledge and forthright with their questions.

Position Summary

This position will support the International Trade Practice by collecting, organizing, and analyzing large amounts of economic and accounting data. The primary responsibilities will be participating on teams of attorneys and other professionals to represent clients in trade litigation (antidumping and countervailing duty proceedings) conducted by the U.S. Department of Commerce, U.S. International Trade Commission, and foreign governments. Assignments can also include proceedings relating to intellectual property infringement, collection of duties by U.S. Customs and Border Protection, and U.S. Treasury disclosures. The analyst will interact directly with international clients and travel to their locations.

Duties and Accountabilities 1
â€¢ Assist in statistical analysis of data related to international trade (sales and cost accounting data of corporations, import statistics , etc.).
â€¢ Provide analytical and strategic input for preparing and verifying antidumping and countervailing duty questionnaires.
â€¢ Perform SAS programming and calculations related to cases.
â€¢ Interact with a variety of software and web-based tools, including internally hosted products (e.g. share-point, hi-q, e-discovery platforms), domestic or foreign government based websites, and client hosted data storage/collection.
â€¢ Collaborate in teams along with attorneys, fellow analysts, and economists in White & Case's offices in Washington D.C., Europe and Asia.

Qualifications
â€¢ Four year college degree with a minimum G.P.A. of 3.5.
â€¢ Advanced degree in math, economics, statistics, computer science, or social sciences with quantitative analysis a plus.
â€¢ At least 3-5 years relevant work experience.
â€¢ Background in accounting and familiarity working with SAP accounting modules a plus.
â€¢ Excellent computer skills, including advanced level knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite - Excel and Access.
â€¢ Strong familiarity with advanced data manipulation functions.
â€¢ Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and present significant amounts of information.
â€¢ Strong attention to detail and accuracy.
â€¢ A drive for identifying the most effective and accurate reporting solutions.
â€¢ Programming experience preferred (VB, SAS, R, etc.).
â€¢ Proficient writing skills.
â€¢ Interest in working with international clients with diverse data processing capabilities.
â€¢ Willingness and ability to work long hours, as needed.
â€¢ Foreign language skills a plus (particularly proficiency in Spanish and/or Portuguese).

: United States-Washington D.C.

Job Description

Program of Instruction (POI)

This is an UNPAID internship through the DoD SkillBridge Program for transitioning active-duty US military personnel. DoD SkillBridge Internships are available to help transitioning active-duty military personnel gain real-world experience in the work force sometime during their final 180 days of active-duty service. The intern will actively train on meaningful projects and work closely with a mentor and with senior company leadership. HII Mission Technologies Internship programs are focused on placing transitioning military into internships that require KSAs, Education & Military Training similar to their current or previous military jobs; positions that could easily transition over to a full-time regular and permanent job with HII.
