title: Solar analyst
description:
Solar Analyst - European Markets

Job Description...

We are seeking an experienced and knowledgeable freelance Solar Analyst to join our team - experience in European markets is a must!

As a Solar Analyst, you will play a crucial role in assessing the viability of land polygons as potential solar projects. Your expertise will help identify the most suitable locations for solar farms.

Responsibilities:

- Conduct in-depth analysis of land polygons using geospatial data, satellite imagery, and relevant datasets.

- Evaluate the feasibility and potential of each polygon for solar energy projects based on factors such as solar irradiation, land characteristics, shading, zoning regulations, and environmental considerations.

- Utilize industry-specific software and tools to assess the financial viability and potential returns on investment for solar projects.

- Prepare comprehensive reports and presentations highlighting your findings, including the technical and financial aspects of each evaluated polygon.

- Collaborate with the team to refine and improve the assessment methodology, incorporating new data sources and algorithms.

Requirements:

- Proven experience in the European solar energy industry, specifically in solar project analysis and site assessment.

- Strong knowledge of geospatial analysis, GIS software, and related tools.

- Familiarity with solar resource assessment methodologies, financial modeling, and economic feasibility analysis.

- Proficiency in interpreting and analyzing satellite imagery, maps, and relevant geospatial datasets

title: Data Analyst/BI
description:
Exciting opportunity for a Business Intelligence Analyst specializing in Financial Modelling and Data Analysis within our Commercial Property company. If you have a passion for building financial models and conducting data analysis, this role is tailor-made for you!

Job Description...

In this position, you will be responsible for developing and adapting financial models, as well as conducting commercial data analysis, including socio-economic demographic research. Your primary focus will be supporting the Commercial Property & Investment teams in business case development and long-term forecasting, spanning up to 20 years.

Additionally, you will create financial models to support business case pitches for property development and fundraising initiatives. Your role will involve developing and maintaining property and demographic long-term models, acting as a bridge between the Operations team (property development) and the Investment/Funds team (modelling).

Given the deepening affordable housing crisis in 2023, along with our ongoing major projects and pitches, joining us at this crucial time will enable you to make a real impact!

Your key responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

Business case development: Budgeting and forecasting

â€¢ Collaborate with business development stakeholders (Commercial Property Operations) and Investments (Funds & Legal) to establish new or update existing business case financial models, feasibility studies, cash-flow forecasts, and assumptions.

â€¢ Build clear and comprehensible financial models, using "plain English," to calculate essential business case metrics such as IRR, NPV, NOI, NAV, ROE, ROIC, Yield, cap rate, and payback period. Incorporate iterative outcomes through sensitivity analysis.

â€¢ Serve as a conduit between the Commercial Property Operations team and the Funds Investment modelling team, ensuring seamless provision of inputs for frequent model-refreshing.

â€¢ Present an overview of key assumptions and outcomes to senior stakeholders, effectively conveying essential points through PowerPoint and Word.

â€¢ Research & Analysis of Socio-Economic Demographics:

â€¢ Thoroughly research and filter relevant socio-economic statistics and data, aligning them with our business target demographics.

â€¢ Present a comprehensive overview of this information, including key assumptions and outcomes, to senior stakeholders using audio-visual means such as Zoom, as well as in Excel, PowerPoint, Word, and PDF formats.

Business Cases & Pitches

â€¢ Provide ad hoc support to the Investment Modelling team to continuously enhance the corporate long-term model and contribute to pitches and presentations.

â€¢ Develop and maintain up-to-date socio-economic statistics and data.

â€¢ Assist in the development of systems, processes, and documentation manuals, detailing workflows and reporting procedures as needed.

Requirements: To be successful in this role, you should possess:

â€¢ Tertiary qualifications in Accounting, Commerce, Finance, Economics, or a related field (desirable but not essential).

â€¢ Minimum of 2 years of experience in financial modelling within the investment field, preferably with exposure to analysis and modelling for construction/property development businesses or equivalent involvement in real estate and population/anthropological studies.

â€¢ Proven experience in developing and maintaining clear and transparent financial models (no black box modelling).

â€¢ Minimum of 2 years of experience working with electronic document management systems.

â€¢ At least 2 years of professional office experience, including modelling and data analysis.

â€¢ Advanced knowledge of Excel (absolutely essential), Word, PowerPoint, and Outlook applications.

â€¢ Proficiency in creating and delivering PowerPoint, PDF, and Excel presentations both in person and through audio-visual platforms.

â€¢ Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.

â€¢ Persistence, patience, and a commitment to accuracy.

â€¢ Effective verbal and written communication skills.

â€¢ Regular and ad hoc reporting to management.

â€¢ Efficient management of workflow process documentation.

â€¢ Ability to work collaboratively as part of a team

title: Data Analyst/BI
description:
Exciting opportunity for a Business Intelligence Analyst specializing in Financial Modelling and Data Analysis within our Commercial Property company. If you have a passion for building financial models and conducting data analysis, this role is tailor-made for you!

Job Description...

In this position, you will be responsible for developing and adapting financial models, as well as conducting commercial data analysis, including socio-economic demographic research. Your primary focus will be supporting the Commercial Property & Investment teams in business case development and long-term forecasting, spanning up to 20 years.

Additionally, you will create financial models to support business case pitches for property development and fundraising initiatives. Your role will involve developing and maintaining property and demographic long-term models, acting as a bridge between the Operations team (property development) and the Investment/Funds team (modelling).

Given the deepening affordable housing crisis in 2023, along with our ongoing major projects and pitches, joining us at this crucial time will enable you to make a real impact!

Your key responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

Business case development: Budgeting and forecasting

â€¢ Collaborate with business development stakeholders (Commercial Property Operations) and Investments (Funds & Legal) to establish new or update existing business case financial models, feasibility studies, cash-flow forecasts, and assumptions.

â€¢ Build clear and comprehensible financial models, using "plain English," to calculate essential business case metrics such as IRR, NPV, NOI, NAV, ROE, ROIC, Yield, cap rate, and payback period. Incorporate iterative outcomes through sensitivity analysis.

â€¢ Serve as a conduit between the Commercial Property Operations team and the Funds Investment modelling team, ensuring seamless provision of inputs for frequent model-refreshing.

â€¢ Present an overview of key assumptions and outcomes to senior stakeholders, effectively conveying essential points through PowerPoint and Word.

â€¢ Research & Analysis of Socio-Economic Demographics:

â€¢ Thoroughly research and filter relevant socio-economic statistics and data, aligning them with our business target demographics.

â€¢ Present a comprehensive overview of this information, including key assumptions and outcomes, to senior stakeholders using audio-visual means such as Zoom, as well as in Excel, PowerPoint, Word, and PDF formats.

Business Cases & Pitches

â€¢ Provide ad hoc support to the Investment Modelling team to continuously enhance the corporate long-term model and contribute to pitches and presentations.

â€¢ Develop and maintain up-to-date socio-economic statistics and data.

â€¢ Assist in the development of systems, processes, and documentation manuals, detailing workflows and reporting procedures as needed.

Requirements: To be successful in this role, you should possess:

â€¢ Tertiary qualifications in Accounting, Commerce, Finance, Economics, or a related field (desirable but not essential).

â€¢ Minimum of 2 years of experience in financial modelling within the investment field, preferably with exposure to analysis and modelling for construction/property development businesses or equivalent involvement in real estate and population/anthropological studies.

â€¢ Proven experience in developing and maintaining clear and transparent financial models (no black box modelling).

â€¢ Minimum of 2 years of experience working with electronic document management systems.

â€¢ At least 2 years of professional office experience, including modelling and data analysis.

â€¢ Advanced knowledge of Excel (absolutely essential), Word, PowerPoint, and Outlook applications.

â€¢ Proficiency in creating and delivering PowerPoint, PDF, and Excel presentations both in person and through audio-visual platforms.

â€¢ Strong organizational skills and attention to detail.

â€¢ Persistence, patience, and a commitment to accuracy.

â€¢ Effective verbal and written communication skills.

â€¢ Regular and ad hoc reporting to management.

â€¢ Efficient management of workflow process documentation.

â€¢ Ability to work collaboratively as part of a team

Under moderate supervision, the Workflow Systems Configuration Analyst I is responsible for working with business teams in defining and maintaining Windward Workflow configuration, including queues, reject codes, reject actions and pends, key words, suspend reasons, RFS codes, holds, queue security, and other configuration data that drives claims processing. The Workflow Systems... Configuration Analyst I is also responsible for defining and maintaining system reference, global system settings and building bulk data loads for other configuration data such as fees and client data, and ensuring proper use of core systems functionality in alignment with corporate goals. â€¢ Strong organizational and prioritization skills.

We depend on our people for our ability to provide the highest-quality benefit programs and superior customer service. description:
Company Profile

Oceaneering is a global provider of engineered services and products, primarily to the offshore energy industry. We develop products and services for use throughout the lifecycle of an offshore oilfield, from drilling to decommissioning. We operate the world's premier fleet of work class ROVs. Additionally, we are a leader in offshore oilfield maintenance services, umbilicals... subsea hardware, and tooling. We also use applied technology expertise to serve the defense, entertainment, material handling, aerospace, science, and renewable energy industries.

Position Summary

The Survey Data Analyst is responsible for data processing and analysis activities required for job preparation, field support, office QC, final reporting QC, final deliverable QC, and project close out activities. This position will remotely connect to our facilities globally to process of ROV and AUV pipeline surveys, as well as conventional geo-hazard multi-beam surveys.

As part of the global approach, the Survey Data Analyst will assist in processing of data and coordinate these efforts with team members in other regions. This position interfaces closely with the offshore staff, GIS, and Project Management teams to support a range of survey efforts and deliverables.

Everyday activities may include, but are not limited to, data processing and analysis support for photogrammetry and subsea pipeline surveys (As-Laid, As-Built, Inspection and Out of Straightness) using multibeam echosounders and LIDARs, as well as geophysical route surveys.

title: Data Annotation Analyst
description:
Description

Help us grow into an ever-evolving marketplace. Seeking an experienced Data Annotation Analyst...

What We Do

Betterview is the Property Intelligence & Risk Management Platform leading the P&C insurance companies depend on to identify and mitigate risk, improve operational and inspection efficiency, and build a more transparent customer experience throughout the policy lifecycle. By empowering insurers to automate pricing, underwriting and renewal while focusing on strategic action on critical properties, Betterview is transforming the insurance industry from Repair and Replace to Predict and Prevent. Combining continuously evolving AI, predictive analysis, computer vision, and customizable workflows to geospatial with commercial, private and public data, Betterview supports your businessesâ€™ unique needs through transparent, actionable, property insights.

Every day, our diverse team is focused on the needs of our customers. We strive to earn their trust by providing valuable, accurate insight that is important to their businesses. We provide our customers with information that is not only useful to their business decisions but easy to use. We combine high quality human interactions with sleek, intuitive design and are pioneers on the journey alongside our customers, who are transforming the way they do business with data-driven decision making.

THE OPPORTUNITYWe are seeking a Data Annotation Analyst who will support the data labeling operations that enable Betterview to continually expand and enrich our training datasets. The analyst will lead the execution of our vendor labeling pipeline from project upload to post-delivery analysis. This role will also provide analysis of our existing data and present quality improvement suggestions to the team. For example, if Betterview were looking for more imagery containing solar panels on a roof, the analyst position supports these efforts by reviewing/cleaning data, preparing it for outside labeling and ingesting it into machine learning workflows. This position reports to the Data Annotation Manager.

â€¢ Identifying opportunities for improvement of methods and processes to ensure data quality and consistency.

title: Compliance Data Analyst
description:
Compliance Data Analyst Role

Job Description...

Sezzle is a cutting-edge fintech company whose mission is to financially empower young consumers. Only one in three millennials own a credit card, and the vast majority of millennials possess a subprime credit score or no score at all. To address these problems, Sezzle has built a payment platform that increases purchasing power for consumers by offering interest-free installment plans at online stores. This increase in purchasing power for consumers leads to increased sales and basket sizes for the hundreds of eCommerce merchants that currently work with Sezzle.

Sezzle is seeking a Data Analyst to drive business success with analytics. This is a quantitative and technical role: you will code, and you will code a lot. This is a collaborative role: you will talk and you will listen; you will teach and you will learn. You'll be responsible for quantitative operational, financial and strategic analytics & reporting. You will collaborate closely with business leaders to create, drive, implement and measure solutions. Teams you may collaborate with can include Product, Engineering, Finance, Sales, Marketing, Support, Legal, Compliance and People Operations.

What Makes Working at Sezzle Awesome?

At Sezzle, we are more than just brilliant engineers, passionate data enthusiasts, out-of-the-box thinkers, and determined innovators; we are skilled musicians, yogis, cyclists, chefs, golfers, dog-lovers, and rock-climbers. We believe in surrounding ourselves with not only the best and the brightest individuals, but those that are unique and purpose-driven in all that they do. Sezzle recognizes and values the importance of diversity and inclusion in enriching the employment experience of its employees and in supporting our mission. Our culture is not defined by a certain set of perks designed to give the illusion of the traditional startup culture, but rather, it is the visible example living in every employee that we hire.

Key Responsibilities Include:
â€¢ Work closely with business teams to understand their priorities and analytics needs
â€¢ Create sophisticated analyses and reporting to provide insights at scale that support growth strategies and empower data-informed decision-making
â€¢ Visualize and articulate analytics results to make it easy for stakeholders to interpret and take actions
â€¢ Help stakeholders identify new opportunities through data analysis
â€¢ Create, monitor, review, and analyze reports and dashboards, take initiative to fix issues that arise and conduct root cause analyses

Minimum Requirements:
â€¢ Degree in statistics, math, finance, economics, data science, computer science or related quantitative discipline
â€¢ 1+ years of professional experience working with data, which can include: complex dataset creation, reporting, profiling, and machine learning
â€¢ Expert in using SQL to extract data and create actionable data sets
â€¢ Experience with Python for data processing and analytics
â€¢ Ability to complete analyses with minimal guidance
â€¢ Experience with data visualization tools such as Redash, Tableau, Looker or Power BI
â€¢ Comfortable making impactful decisions in a fast-paced and sometimes ambiguous environment, able to pivot quickly to new priorities
â€¢ Attention to detail and ability to multitask
â€¢ Excellent problem-solving skills.
â€¢ Strong business judgment and communication skills

Preferred Knowledge and Skills:
â€¢ Graduate degree in a quantitative discipline
â€¢ Experience optimizing operational and financial performance
â€¢ Experience in payments, financial services, banking, fintech, BNPL, etc...

The Tech You'll Work With:
â€¢ Python
â€¢ Redshift, PostgreSQL, MySQL
â€¢ Data build tool (dbt)
â€¢ AWS, G Suite, Mac

Interview Process:
â€¢ Online assessment
â€¢ Conversation with our recruiter.
â€¢ SQL interview with Coderpad. Share your SQL knowledge.
â€¢ Verbal case study interview. Share how you approach new problems. A "How would youâ€¦" conversation.
â€¢ Verbal behavioral interview. Share your problem-solving experience. A "Tell me about a time when youâ€¦" conversation.

About You:
â€¢ A+ character. We are team-first here at Sezzle.
â€¢ A hard-working mentality. It's early and there is still a lot to build.
â€¢ An excellent communicator.
â€¢ A fun attitude. Life's too short. We can have fun while we work hard on cool things.
â€¢ Smarts. We need people that are smart enough to make decisions on their own and also smart enough to know when they need input from others.

Perks and Benefits:
â€¢ Competitive salary, bonus, and benefits
â€¢ Generous stock options
â€¢ Medical, dental and vision insurance
â€¢ Life and long term disability insurance
â€¢ 401k with match
â€¢ The opportunity to join Minneapolis's fastest growing startup alongside a team of motivated and driven individuals

Sezzle provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, and related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, genetic information or characteristics, marital status, familial status, veteran or military status, status regarding public assistance, membership or activity in a local commission, or any other protected status in accordance with applicable federal, state and local laws.

The compensation range for the role is $75,000- $95,000 (inclusive only of base salary, and exclusive of other potential competitive benefits such as on-target commission, bonus payments, and equity). title: Associate Research/Data Analyst (OEWS)
description:
Why Youâ€™ll Love Working For This Department

You will be joining a Department committed to a culture of TEAMWORK to accomplish our goals together, where we deliver excellence through COLLABORATION with partners and stakeholders, embody ACCOUNTABILITY through trust and professionalism, and embrace WORK-LIFE BALANCE by prioritizing respect, boundaries, and time. While working at DHEWD you will be... helping to develop the workforce of the future! Join us as we pursue our vision of â€œEvery Missourian empowered with the skills and education needed for success.â€

Focus of the Position: This position works within Missouriâ€™s Occupational Employment and Wage Statistics (OEWS) team, a program administered by the Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS). The OEWS unit is housed in the Missouri Economic Research and Information Center (MERIC), which is the state cooperative partner to BLS and the labor market information agency responsible for measuring labor market activity and the economy in Missouri. OEWS collects data related to the number of workers in Missouri and the wage ranges by occupation in nonagricultural industries. This information is used for analysis of the occupational composition of different industries, for determining national policy related to structural unemployment, and for other purposes such as training and employment planning at state and local levels. As a member of this team, you will be responsible for reaching out to Missouri employers that have been sampled to gather their data. Contacts will be through phone calls, emails, mailings, and the BLS portal. The position allows an opportunity to work together as a team and to work independently to get assigned tasks completed. Candidates interested in this position should be flexible and able to adjust as the demand and focus on work shifts.

What Youâ€™ll Do

To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential function of the job with or without reasonable accommodation.
â€¢ Collect detailed occupational employment and wage information for Missouri employers through the phone, email, and other collection methods.
â€¢ Analyze job classification information by understanding and utilizing the Standard Occupational Classification (SOC) system and industry classification information by using the North American Classification System (NAICS) received from the US Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics.
â€¢ Properly track and enter activity into the data collection software system.
â€¢ Analyze returned employer reports for data quality, accuracy, and completeness.
â€¢ Develop and maintain working knowledge of staffing patterns, occupational differences, and occupational coding systems, as well as industry classifications, in order to solicit and properly code survey responses.
â€¢ Proficiently use programs used in the OEWS Program, including Word, Excel, and other program specific software.
â€¢ Follow guidelines and requirements put forth by the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics in the Cooperative Agreement with the State of Missouri.
â€¢ Answer questions regarding the program and how the data is used and the importance of it.
â€¢ Research employers to find information related to them, including contact information and the industry they are in.
â€¢ Other duties related to the collection and coding of data for the OEWS program.
â€¢ Perform other related work as assigned.
â€¢ Demonstrate regular and reliable attendance.

Minimum Qualifications
â€¢ A Bachelorâ€™s degree from an accredited college or university including or supplemented by three earned credit hours in statistics or research methods.

Technical and/or professional experience in a related field may substitute on a year-for-year basis for deficiencies in the required college education

More Reasons To Love This Position

The State of Missouri offers an excellent benefits package that includes a defined pension plan, generous amounts of leave and holiday time, and eligibility for health insurance coverage. Your total compensation is more than the dollars you receive in your paycheck. To help demonstrate the value of working for the State of Missouri, we have created an interactive Total Compensation Calculator. This tool provides a comprehensive view of benefits and more that are offered to prospective employees. The Total Compensation Calculator and other applicant resources can be found here .

The State of Missouri is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees

title: Data Analyst (Remote)
description:
ABOUT THE ORGANIZATION:

Manufacturers Bank was formed by a group of banking entrepreneurs in June 1962. Our scope is to serve the specialized needs of California middle-market businesses, manufacturers, wholesalers, distributors, importers, exporters, and service companies, including small businesses and professionals...

Our mission is to be "the bank of choice" for middle market and professional service companies by establishing long term customer relationships and loyalty, providing superior products and services through a core of highly skilled and seasoned bankers.

To achieve our mission to be the 'bank of choice' for middle market and professional services companies, we are focused on our vision to be the premier California regional business bank that can provide the sophistication and expertise of a larger institution with the personal 'high touch' services of a smaller bank.

Specialties:

Commercial Loans and Lines of Credit, Asset-Based Financing, SBA Loans, and Specialized Financing, Real Estate Loans, Cash Management Services, International Services

NEW DIGITAL BANK MISSION STATEMENT:

Join us on our mission to create a completely new, 100% digital bank that truly serves customersâ€™ best interests. We are a close knit and fun-loving team of seasoned financial services professionals who came together for the challenge of building a bank from scratch â€“ and we are committed to doing it all the right way (from technology infrastructure to modern marketing to customer experience).

We work with the flexibility and speed of start-up. But we also have significant stability and capital from being part of the SMBC Group (Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation). SMBC is the 2nd largest bank in Japan, and the 12th largest bank in the world with operations in over 40 countries. And SMBC is committed to disrupting the US marketplace with ground-breaking products.

Itâ€™s the best of both worlds, and we are seeking proven marketing leaders to propel us towards national launch. We have both the ambitious growth plans and the â€œpatient capitalâ€ necessary to execute a multi-year plan. Join us on the journey to deliver an exciting concept of evolved banking.

JOB SUMMARY:

Reporting to the SVP, Deposit and Lending Operations Executive, this position will support the insourced operational needs of the Deposits, Lending, Call Center, and Account Application Operations Leaders. The Data Analyst will support a broad range of operations and operational oversight functions for the team.

The Challenge: At launch, our data warehouse will not yet be in place. You will source data from various de-centralized sources to create reporting and visualizations. You will have the experience and imagination necessary to efficiently create and provide this analysis. Your skills with Python, SQL, Power BI, or Google Analytics will help you here. As the Data Warehouse is built, you will be our key source of report building and analysis from this environment. Your skills with analysis and lean thinking will now come into play as you apply DMAIC to identify and improve processes. Eventually, this positions journey will lead towards Machine Learning and Robotics, with tools such as Automation Anywhere or Blue Prism, to automate functions and build efficiency.

Who you are: You likely have a couple of years of experience and are a fan of data and data analysis tools and continuous improvement. You have these skills and certifications as a minimum. You might already be on a Six Sigma or Lean certification path. You know the future is automation, and you either have skills in this field, or plan to have them on your educational journey.

PRINCIPAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
â€¢ Develop and manage programs/initiatives for data quality, change control, governance.
â€¢ Identify, manage, and review data quality metrics for internal and external reporting and provide input into communication routines with stakeholders, business partners, and senior leaders.
â€¢ Design and conduct analysis to identify and remediate change controls, data quality, or integrity issues to identify and remediate process or control gaps.
â€¢ Analyze, assess, and test data controls and data systems to ensure quality and risk compliance standards are met including developing recommendations for optimal approaches to resolve data quality issues.
â€¢ Execute internal data quality audits to benchmark the state of data quality.
â€¢ Provide key support to JB Audit and RCSA activities.
â€¢ Assists VP, and AVPs with developing and maintaining the Risk Control Self-Assessment.
â€¢ Work with business and technology partners or subject matter professionals to document or maintain business or data elements or data-related controls.
â€¢ Consult with internal partners to assess the current state of data quality within the area of assigned responsibility.
â€¢ Recommend plans for the development and implementation of initiatives that assess the quality of new data sources.
â€¢ Plan and support implementation of data migration to new tooling including drafting requirements, performing assessments on quality of new data sources, designing, and supporting cross functional user testing.

POSITION SPECIFICATIONS:

Education: College Degree

Experience, Skills & Qualifications:
â€¢ Minimum 2+ years of Data Management and Business Analytics.
â€¢ Experience, or equivalent demonstrated through one or a combination of the following: work experience, training, military experience, or education.
â€¢ Experience working in Operations and/or reporting environment.
â€¢ Knowledge and understanding of audit, regulatory compliance, or risk management is a nice to have.
â€¢ Experience analyzing and documenting workflow, processes, and procedures.
â€¢ Experience working with workflow management tools (Jira, Confluence, Miro).
â€¢ Data analytics experience (Tableau, Power BI, Python, SQL, Google Analytics development experience preferred).
â€¢ Excellent MS Office skills

â€¢ Convert existing datasets from a diverse array of file formats (e.g., Microsoft Excel, Access, and SQL) into analytic datasets.

â€¢ Program SAS checks to integrate and reconcile data from US states and US Territories.

Discretionary
Summary

At BOK Financial, our success starts with our incredible talent. Are you an experienced Technical Analyst who enjoys problem solving? We are looking for someone who finds satisfaction in helping others by offering sound advice and places great value on building meaningful relationships. If that describes you, then bring your knowledge, skills, and abilities to us as a Technical Analyst III in our Enterprise Data Solutions Team. Youâ€™ll be positioned for a great career!
Job Description

Primarily responsible for supporting mission critical application systems software and interfaces requiring high technical and systems knowledge along with advanced troubleshooting skills. Provide day-to-day support for complex applications systems including supporting business users working with multiple internal and external applications with critical interfaces having a significant direct impact to our customers. Help enable business success and create raving fans with business users by providing top notch support for systems including coordinating and participating in development, testing, disaster recovery planning/testing, change management/deployment, and daily support.

The Technical Analyst III job family is responsible for delivering superior services acting as a liaison between the line of business and IT with a focus on end user experience such as user interfacing, user flow, data flow. Using comprehensive expertise, defining and performing analysis, design, programming, planning, implementation, and supporting of some of the most critical systems software and procedures with a focus on our long term technology road map which require technical and systems knowledge.
Team Culture

Our team is committed to delivering the best IT solutions for our lines of business. We collaborate with other IT members, as well as our business partners. It is a fast-paced, ever-changing yet fun environment with a number of new exciting initiatives. The mission of IT is to Enable Business Success and Create Raving fans. We do this through our shared quest to continuously improve, while simultaneously looking at ways to optimize our applications and processes. We are a determined, smart, and collaborative group that is eager to welcome you to the team.
How You'll Spend Your Time

You will utilize your knowledge of troubleshooting to take on day-to-day support of mission critical applications and support and develop simple to complex stored procedures and provide technical requirements/specifications.

You will actively partner and collaborate with Technical teams and Vendors, data acquisition and information delivery.

You will perform job scheduling responsibilities including writing, reading, and troubleshooting job plan; while also understanding and creating data flow documentation (includes data mapping and conversion mapping) for complexity ranging from single application data flow to multiple application data flows.

You will be responsible for complex systems process analysis, testing, implementation, configuration, deployments, and disaster recovery. Employ IT governance policies and technology standards.

You will have experienced technical understanding of multiple application data flows across multiple applications, software and system integrations, tiered environments.

You will track metrics and trends of application performance and remediate issues. Develop and maintain application documentation; define and maintain application configuration.

You will drive change control processes as applied to supported applications and projects; drive support incident management.

Education & Experience Requirements

This level of knowledge is normally acquired through completion of (a/an) Bachelorâ€™s Degree in Information Technology or Computer Science or related field of study and / or 8-10 years of directly related experience in Technical Analysis, Data Analytics, or Bank Operations or equivalent combination of education and experience.

â€¢ Experience working with a large data warehouse is highly preferable.
â€¢ Following problems thru to resolution - this is not just making sure a job finishes for the day. Its digging deeper into why there was a problem, doing all that can be done to avoid this in the future, with code changes, process changes etc. and then Documenting in detail the issue and resolve.
â€¢ Willing to learn and accepting that we all have knowledge limitations, being proactive in setting up meetings etc. to learn more on how applications work, and how to handle problems when they arise on our (support team) own.
â€¢ Ability to prioritize work in a Tiered environment
â€¢ Oral and written communication skills to effectively communicate issues and explain resolutions
â€¢ Willing to learn applications used internally such as AWA (Job Scheduling software). Power BI, etc.
â€¢ Ability to take initiative as you focus on the desired deliverables, while meeting and exceeding your goals.
â€¢ A background with tracking and solving complex problems in a variety of situations and function effectively in rapidly changing or unclear conditions.

title: Data Analyst
description:
Spreedly is the world's leading Payments Orchestration solution. Our vision is that the world is better with a diversified, inclusive payment ecosystem. Our mission is to accelerate commerce with an open, secure, and flexible payment platform that welcomes all payment participants. Backed by Spectrum Equity, with a $75M investment, Spreedly is experiencing rapid growth.

We now serve 600... customers globally. Many of these direct customers are platforms and marketplaces that have thousands of their merchants leveraging our payments platform. Our customers include industry leaders in digital goods, order ahead and delivery, online marketplaces, donation/giving platforms, event ticketing, and financial services.

Our employees help us execute against our vision through building a culture focused on autonomy, transparency, and collaboration in a dynamic, high-growth organization.

We are seeking a Data Analyst to join our growing Business Analytics team. As a Data Analyst at Spreedly, you will work alongside a group of self-starters interested in solving real-world problems and in streamlining our internal capacity to simplify a complex environment with billions of data points and improve an industry by analyzing the new operating system for payments.

The ideal candidate is a data-obsessed, versatile professional who is passionate about telling data stories to non-technical audiences. They are able to call on their deep technical expertise and business knowledge to advance our capabilities to synthesize large volumes of complex big data and refine that raw data into actionable visual insights that are meaningful and important to the business. They will also work with business leaders and managers to use data to drive executive-level decision making, collaborating to build a data-driven culture within Spreedly.

Responsibilities
â€¢ Exercise all phases of business analysis, including data quality, data analysis, data visualization, and presentation of results and deliverables
â€¢ Build a positive relationship with business partners to provide operational/useful insights to improve business critical metrics with a focus on the growth of the business
â€¢ Explain trends across data sources, potential opportunities for growth or improvement, and data caveats for descriptive, diagnostic, predictive (including forecasting), and prescriptive data analysis
â€¢ Participate in the creation and support of analytics standards and best practices
â€¢ Utilize code (Python/R/SQL) for data analysis
â€¢ Explain trends across data sources, potential opportunities for growth or improvement, and data caveats for descriptive, diagnostic, predictive (including forecasting), and prescriptive data analysis
â€¢ Partner with product and engineering teams to design tests (A/B, multivariate, etc.), track and measure the results, and analyze the results to quantify the impact on the business
â€¢ Conduct revenue optimization & product early-life usage analysis to guide the growth & marketing team initiatives
â€¢ Provide ad hoc reports as requested to support internal business units

Requirements
â€¢ 5+ years working in data or analytics, with experience in a SaaS environment
â€¢ Experience analyzing payments industry-specific data is required for this role
â€¢ Experience with Looker, GitHub, and DBT (or a similar tool)
â€¢ Hands-on experience coding with R or Python and working with API calls and JSON to generate business insights and drive better organizational decision-making
â€¢ Knowledge of key SaaS metrics and product benchmarks (DAU/MAU, user retention, etc.)
â€¢ Experience with both pre- and post-sales analytics and go-to-market metrics such as conversion, churn, NRR, LTV, etc.
â€¢ Have solid project management skills, including planning work, managing details, keeping multiple tasks/projects on track, working with cross-functional stakeholders, and navigating ambiguity to deliver results
â€¢ Enthusiasm for conducting reproducible analysis, code reviews, version control, and solid documentation
â€¢ Bachelor's degree in a quantitative or technical field

What We Offer
â€¢ Competitive salary + Equity
â€¢ Outstanding Medical and Dental Insurance: Premiums are 100% company paid for employees and families
â€¢ Note: We offer two PPO health insurance plans: A traditional copay and a high deductible with HSA. Spreedly contributes $1,200/$2,400 per year to the HSA for those choosing the high deductible plan
â€¢ Life and long-term disability insurance
â€¢ Optional Vision insurance and various Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA)
â€¢ Open Paid Time Off policy + 12 weeks paid leave for new parents
â€¢ Matching 401k plan (5% up to $5,000 yearly)
â€¢ Monthly digital lifestyle stipend ($150), new MacBook, and $200 accessory reimbursement
â€¢ $3,000 annual Professional Development stipend and free LinkedIn Learning subscription
â€¢ Flexible, remote friendly work environment
â€¢ Quarterly visits to HQ in Durham, NC for remote employees

Spreedly is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to fostering, cultivating and preserving a culture of diversity, equity and inclusion. We actively work to drive out even unintentional discrimination in our hiring processes via practices like blindly graded work samples, structured interviews, and diversity awareness training.

Due to the sensitive nature of what Spreedly does - handling payment data - finalist candidates must complete a successful background and reference check.

Some of our positions are open to remote applicants. If this is the case it will be sited in the job posting just below the position name. Unless otherwise stated, remote positions are open to candidates in the contiguous US only. We are not set up to support remote employees from CA, NY, or outside the contiguous US. All applicants must have a US work visa.

We appreciate your interest in our company. Because of the high volume of resume flow, we may only respond to those candidates that we think will be a potential fit.

title: Data Engineer and Analyst for a growing startup to build a data...
description:
GeoSnapShot is a global sports photography selling platform. We're all about empowering professional & amateur photographers to earn money by selling captivating photos of participants in sporting events. We support some of the largest brands and up & coming photographers in the US, UK, Europe & Australia.

...

Our data problems: We have a transactional database powering our web product with a couple of analysis tools hooked up (Holistics & Metabase). We do not have a semantic model layer that enables non-technical members of our organization to run quick reports. If we find the right fit, this will be an ongoing part-time engagement to support the data platform and also build one-off reporting for our business.

2. Fluency with SQL

3. Experience building ETL/ELT pipelines preferably on AWS cloud.

4. Expertise with dbt and other data modeling/transformation tools.

5. Experience building and supporting self-serve analytics suites for business users.

6. Expertise in any BI systems: Tableau, QuickSight, Holitics, Mode, etc

For more than 30 years, ISC has utilized a unique... bottom-up approach to ensure solutions emerge from within communities, rather than being imposed from the outside.

Through a deep understanding of and commitment to communities that are the least likely to cause global climate change yet face the highest impacts, ISC develops creative and inclusive solutions, demonstrated in our work in the US and across Asia in China, India, the Mekong, and Bangladesh.  - Contract to Hire
description:
We are a dynamic and innovative organization in Digital PR seeking a highly skilled and motivated Data Analyst to work with us on an ad hoc basis. We specialize in tailoring and implementing growth strategies, leveraging compelling content, and utilizing data-driven digital PR backlinks to drive high-quality, converting traffic for SaaS and B2B companies. As an Ad Hoc Data Analyst, you will have... the opportunity to collaborate with us on specific projects, providing valuable data analysis and insights to support our business goals.

Job Description:

You will be responsible for performing data analysis and providing insights for specific projects as assigned. You will work closely with our team, utilizing your analytical skills and expertise to extract meaningful information from complex datasets. Your work will contribute to evidence-based decision-making and help drive the success of our projects.

Responsibilities:

Data Collection and Extraction:

Collaborate with the team to identify the required data and develop data collection processes.

Extract and gather data from various sources, ensuring data integrity and accuracy.

Data Analysis and Interpretation:

Conduct in-depth data analysis to identify patterns, trends, and correlations. Apply statistical techniques and modeling to derive actionable insights from the data.

Topic Study and Research:

Conduct research on the assigned project topic, leveraging both internal and external resources.

Synthesize relevant information and contribute to the development of research methodologies.

Sample Work Evaluation:

Evaluate and analyze previous sample work to understand its context and relevance to the current project.

Identify potential areas for improvement or optimization based on previous work samples.

Collaboration and Communication:

Collaborate with the team to define project requirements, goals, and deliverables.

Communicate findings and recommendations effectively.

Qualifications:

Proven experience as a Data Analyst or similar role, focusing on data analysis, research, and reporting.

Strong proficiency in data analysis tools and programming languages (e.g., SQL, Python, R, etc.).

Familiarity with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, etc.) and statistical analysis techniques.

Solid understanding of statistical concepts, experimental design, and data modeling. Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to think analytically and critically.

Strong attention to detail and the ability to handle and analyze complex datasets.

Effective communication skills, including the ability to present findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Ability to work on an ad hoc basis and manage multiple projects simultaneously. Familiarity with the Digital PR industry is a plus.

Join us as an Ad Hoc Data Analyst and contribute your expertise to our specific projects. This is an excellent opportunity to work with a dynamic team and gain experience in various areas of data analysis. We offer competitive compensation for ad hoc work and the chance to be part of our innovative projects.

Apply today and become a valuable member of our team

title: Senior Quantitative Analyst, Data Science
description:
About Us

Every day we deliver safe and secure energy to homes, communities, and businesses. We are there when people need us the most. We connect people to the energy they need for the lives they live. The pace of change in society and our industry is accelerating and our expertise and track record puts us in an unparalleled position to shape the sustainable future of our industry...

To be successful we must anticipate the needs of our customers, reducing the cost of energy delivery today and pioneering the flexible energy systems of tomorrow. This requires us to deliver on our promises and always look for new opportunities to grow, both ourselves and our business.

National Grid is hiring a Senior Quantitative Data Scientist of Forecasting. This position will be located in the Hicksville, NY office or Waltham, MA office.

Job Purpose

The Load Forecasting & Analytics team produces electric and gas load forecasts for National Grid. This role will support the delivery of several initiatives within the Load Forecasting & Analytics team that will help modernize National Gridâ€™s electric system in New England creating a network that can accommodate a rising number of distributed energy resources with increased levels of reliability and control. You will develop short term load forecasts and contribute to other projects supporting our forecasting and distributed resource teams. Your key internal stakeholders include Distributed Generation, System Planning, Supply, Engineering and the operational Control Centers. You will ensure that the forecasts incorporate new distributed energy resources, technologies, and policies.

Key Accountabilities
â€¢ Develop and implement short-term load forecast models and processes. Perform analysis relating to the forecast as necessary. Enable processes to be integrated with daily control center operations, distribution planning and supply procurement.
â€¢ Develop short-term forecasts at both the system level and more granular areas such as electric feeders and substations.
â€¢ Short-term forecasting using machine learning, regression analysis, neural nets, trees, etc.
â€¢ The ability to work and defend results. The ability to speak to both technical and non-technical persons to present projects is essential.
â€¢ Ensure the forecasts properly account for distributed energy resources (DERs) and policies (e.g. demand response, electrification, solar, wind).
â€¢ Support other load forecasting teams â€“ long-term electric & gas, data and DERs â€“ on ad hoc and other projects as needed.
â€¢ Implement process improvement and best practices; and remain abreast of changing technologies and industry best practices in order to provide a service that is fit for purpose.
â€¢ Update forecast processes and documentation to ensure they are efficient, and reviewable.
â€¢ Provide expert testimony before regulators and defend the forecasts. Respond to data requests from regulatory bodies for rate cases and other proceedings.
â€¢ Work with internal stakeholders (including planning, supply, engineering, operations) regarding forecast methodology and analysis and ensure our deliverables meet their needs.

Qualifications
â€¢ A Bachelorâ€™s degree (Masterâ€™s preferred) in statistics, applied analytics, engineering, data science or related quantitatively rigorous field.
â€¢ 5 or more years of relevant energy industry experience in a regulated setting is preferred.
â€¢ Demonstrated experience with econometric or statistical forecasting or modelling required. Knowledge in time series, regression, machine learning, neural networks or similar used for forecasting is required. Experience in energy load forecasting preferred.
â€¢ Good understanding of industry operations and the regulatory environment is preferred. Knowledge specific to National Grid is a plus.
â€¢ Experience forecasting short and/or long-term impacts of weather and distributed resources on loads is preferred.
â€¢ Strong written and verbal communication skills including the ability to speak to higher levels of internal leaders, external regulators and other market players. Ability to explain complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
â€¢ Demonstrated experience in modeling with Python and/or R is required. SQL skills preferred. Visualization of results a plus. Knowledge in integrating short-term forecasting processes into company day-to-day operational and IT systems is a plus.
â€¢ Advanced Excel skills required.

More Information

Salary

$123K - $145K a year

This position has a career path which provides for advancement opportunities within and across bands as you develop and evolve in the position; gaining experience, expertise and acquiring and applying technical skills. Candidates will be assessed and provided offers against the minimum qualifications of this role and their individual experience.

LEGENDS

GLOBAL SALES

As an extension of your team, our sales experts work diligently with your management and staff to create solutions and programs that are always fully custom to your needs and goals. Kansas Athletics and Legends, a global premium experiences company, have announced a comprehensive, long-term partnership focused on reimagining the fan experience as part of the expansive renovation of iconic Allen Fieldhouse and the transformation of David Booth Kansas Memorial Stadium.

Allen Fieldhouse, the premier venue in college basketball, will soon undergo a series of renovations that will include upgraded fan experience amenities and reimagined and expanded premium hospitality spaces. This critical role will be focused on ticketing purchases, industry trends, athletic constituent behavior patterns, and historic athletic donation data to further harness, extend and deliver the data analytics to drive business performance in the following verticals: Revenue associated with the Premium Seating, Ticketing, and Fundraising.

To accomplish this task, the Manager of Data, CRM & Analytics works with Ticketing, Marketing, Premium Seating & Athletic Fundraising, and Athletic leaderships to understand, define and document the overarching business objectives. â€¢ Ability to build flexible and innovative strategic plans for how analytics can be leveraged to improve the effectiveness of current campaigns, and to drive insights for new campaigns.

Qualifications

Compensation

title: (USA) Senior Data Analyst with Energy, Utilities and Sustainability
description:
Position Summary...

What you'll do...

Walmart Texas Retail Energy (TRE) manages competitive energy markets at the wholesale and retail level. TRE serves as the 17th largest utility in the US and manages energy needs for Walmart Stores across 12 states. TRE has expertise in market principles and concepts, energy and renewable transactions and pricing strategies, and performs demand side management such as demand response and peak load management. At TRE, we also manage our governance, reports, load forecasts; market settlements; rates; invoicing; payments and systems.

You'll sweep us off our feet if...
â€¢ Experience in Competitive Energy and Wholesale / Retail Energy Markets and knowledge about Sustainability, Renewables and Natural gas functions.
â€¢ Experience in Energy Trading and Risk Management (ETRM) Tools.
â€¢ Experience dealing with Energy utilities EDI (Electronic Data Integration) files.

What Skills you bring...
â€¢ Statistical and Machine Learning models such as Linear... Regression, Decision models, PCA, K-Means etc. using R and Python libraries.
â€¢ Data exploration and Visualization using PowerBI, R plots, Python.
â€¢ Programming and scripting using SQL, VBA, Python, R.
â€¢ Experience in Energy Utilities, Sustainability and Wholesale / retail electricity as well as natural gas market functions.

You'll make an impact by...
â€¢ Develop and strategize data initiatives to support TRE energy and business transformations. Build analytical and empirical data models for market data exploration, rates, pricing, and estimates. Develop key performance indicators to contribute to Walmart Energy sustainability and transformation goals. Analyze and transform business needs to data models. Evaluate data workflows and systems for variances, discrepancies, and efficiencies. Develop story boards, reports, and visualization to transform data events into guided insights for decision making.
â€¢ Data Source Identification: Requires knowledge of Functional business domain (Energy Markets) and scenarios; Categories of data and where it is held; Business data requirements; Database technologies and distributed datastores (e.g. SQL, NoSQL); Data Quality; Existing business systems and processes, including the key drivers and measures of success. To support the understanding of the priority order of requirements and service level agreements. Help identify the most suitable source for data that is fit for purpose. Perform initial data quality checks on extracted data.
â€¢ Data Strategy: Requires knowledge of understanding of business value and relevance of data and data enabled insights / decisions; Appropriate application and understanding of data ecosystem including Data Management, Data Quality Standards and Data Governance, Accessibility, Storage and Scalability, etc.; Understanding of the methods and applications that unlock the monetary value of data assets. To understand, articulate, and apply principles of the defined strategy to routine business problems that involve a single function.
â€¢ Understanding Business Context: Requires knowledge of Industry and environmental factors; Common business vernacular; Business practices across two or more domains such as Energy markets, utilities, finance, technology, business systems, and in-depth knowledge of related practices; Directly relevant business metrics and business areas. To Provide recommendations to business stakeholders to solve complex business issues.
â€¢ Develop business cases for projects with a projected return on investment or cost savings. Translate business requirements into projects, activities, and tasks and aligns to overall business strategy and develops domain specific artifact. Serve as an interpreter and conduit to connect business needs with tangible solutions and results. Identify and recommend relevant business insights pertaining to their area of work.
â€¢ Problem Formulation: Requires knowledge of Analytics/big data analytics / automation techniques and methods; Business understanding; Precedence and use cases; Business requirements and insights. To translate/ co-own business problems within one's discipline to data related or mathematical solutions. Identify appropriate methods/tools to be leveraged to provide a solution for the problem. Share use cases and gives examples to demonstrate how the method would solve the business problem.
â€¢ Data Modeling: Develop, maintain and support logical as well as analytical data models for business processes and reports. Develop semantic layer to perform data analysis and reporting. Develop models to support users with self-service reporting that supports cloud as well on-premise data environment. Collaborate with data integration and BI team to create optimized models. Develop and maintain metadata and data dictionary. Develop machine learning and statistical models to support load-forecasts and estimates using batch as well as real-time data streams.
â€¢ Data Visualization: Requires knowledge of Visualization guidelines and best practices for complex data types; Multiple data visualization tools (for example, Python, R libraries, GGplot, Matplotlib, Ploty, Tableau, PowerBI etc.); Advanced visualization techniques/ tools; Multiple story plots and structures (OABCDE); Communication & influencing technique; Emotional intelligence. To generate appropriate graphical representations of data and model outcomes. Understand customer requirements to design appropriate data representation for multiple data sets. Increase agility for reporting to create visibility and derive valuable insights.
â€¢ Work with User Experience designers and User Interface engineers as required to build front end applications. Present to and influences the team and business audience using the appropriate data visualization frameworks and conveys clear messages through business and stakeholder understanding. Customize communication style based on stakeholder under guidance, and leverages rational arguments. Guide and mentor junior associates on story types, structures, and techniques based on context.
â€¢ Data Quality Management: Requires knowledge of Data quality management techniques and standards; Business metadata definitions and content data definitions; Data profiling tools, data cleansing tools, data integration tools, and issues and event management tools; Understanding of user's data consumption, data needs, and business implications; Data modeling, storage, integration, and warehousing; Data quality framework and metrics; User access best practices; Enterprise data architecture, modeling and design, storage, integration, and warehousing; Enterprise data quality framework and metrics; Enterprise data strategy; Enterprise data quality strategy; Enterprise strategy to address regulatory and ethical requirements and policies around data privacy, security, storage, retention, and documentation. To promote and educate others on data quality awareness. Profile, analyze, and assess data quality. Test and validate data quality requirements. Continuously measure and monitor data quality.
â€¢ Deliver against data quality service level agreements. Manage operational Data Quality Management procedures. Manage data quality issues and leads data cleansing activities to remove data quality defects, improve data quality, and eliminate unused data. Determine user accessibility and removes or restricts user access as needed. Interpret company and regulatory policies on data. Educate others on data governance processes, practices, policies, and guidelines.
â€¢ Exploratory Data Analysis: Requires knowledge of relevant Knowledge Discovery in Data (KDD) tools, applications, or scripting languages such as SQL, MS Excel (VBA), Python; Statistical techniques (for example, mean, mode, median, variance, standard deviation, correlation, and sorting and grouping); Research analysis standards and activities; Documentation procedures such as drafting, editing, Bibliography format; Relevant Knowledge Discovery in Data (KDD) tools, applications, or scripting languages such as SQL, DB, SAS, Oracle, Apache Mahout, MS Excel, Python; KDD industry best practices and emerging trends. To collect and tabulate data and evaluate results to determine accuracy, validity, and applicability.
â€¢ Support the identification and application of statistical techniques based on requirements. Apply suitable technique under direction from leadership. Assist in the planning, design and implementation of an exploratory data analysis research projects. Understand existing statistical models and identify and recommend statistical models based on hypothesis. Use advanced Knowledge in Data Discovery tools to write queries and analyze data to identify patterns, trends, outliers, and correlations. Conduct statistical analysis (for example hypothesis tests, confidence intervals) and build basic statistical models using relevant packages/software suites.
â€¢ Demonstrates up-to-date expertise and applies this to the development, execution, and improvement of action plans by providing expert advice and guidance to others in the application of information and best practices; supporting and aligning efforts to meet customer and business needs; and building commitment for perspectives and rationales. Provides and supports the implementation of business solutions by building relationships and partnerships with key stakeholders; identifying business needs; determining and carrying out necessary processes and practices; monitoring progress and results; recognizing and capitalizing on improvement opportunities; and adapting to competing demands, organizational changes, and new responsibilities.
â€¢ Models compliance with company policies and procedures and supports company mission, values, and standards of ethics and integrity by incorporating these into the development and implementation of business plans; using the Open Door Policy; and demonstrating and assisting others with how to apply these in executing business processes and practices.

Minimum Qualifications...

Outlined below are the required minimum qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no minimum qualifications.

Option 1: Bachelor's degree in Business, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, Analytics, Mathematics, Arts, Finance or related field and 2 years' experience in data analysis, data science, statistics, or related field. Option 2: Master's degree in Business, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, Analytics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Information Technology or related field. Option 3: 4 years' experience in data analysis, data science, statistics, or related field.

Preferred Qualifications...

Outlined below are the optional preferred qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no preferred qualifications.

Data science, data analysis, statistics, or related field, Master's degree in Business, Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, Analytics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Information Technology or related field, Related industry experience (for example, retail, merchandising, healthcare, eCommerce), Successful completion of assessments in data analysis and Business Intelligence tools and scripting languages (for example, SQL, Python, Spark, Scala, R, Power BI, or Tableau)

title: Senior Data Analyst I
description:
Senior Data Analyst I-Continental Resources

Job SummaryThe Senior Data Analyst is primarily responsible for leading projects to automate manual processes and produce data driven insights for the team and other stakeholders across the organization.

A successful candidate will also actively seek out and generate new and innovative ways to retrieve, visualize and analyze data across a variety of operational, geological and financial data sources.
Serves as a resource within functional area. Guides others in resolving complex issues; may lead functional teams or projects. Advanced knowledge of fundamental theories, principles and practices in the area of specialization. Solves complex problems without precedent and/or structure; takes a broad perspective to identify solutions. Works independently, with guidance in complex situations.

Duties and ResponsibilitiesLeads large-scale data & analytics projects across the organizationDiscovers and troubleshoots data issues across sources and... drives issues to resolutionCreate highly complex datasets, visualizations and toolsMentors and trains junior staff; creates training content and executes across the team, department and company.

Collaborate with varying levels of engineers, geologists and management to effectively gather data/reporting requirements and build analytical datasets, visualizations and toolsOwn, maintain and enhance critical Spotfire Tools that are used to run the non-operated businessImplement automated solutions to streamline manual team processesPerform data capture processes as necessary to support analytics effortsPersonal commitment to inclusion and diversityOther duties as assigned.

Skills and Competencies Use SQL to retrieve data from systems, create integrated datasets using CTEs and/or subqueries, update data within systems and create data tables and views within CLR's data warehouseUse Spotfire to enhance existing projects and create new projects from scratch using data from a variety of sources across the enterpriseUnderstands or is able to learn the data models of Continental's primary data sources including Aries, WellView, ProCount, SAP, Planning Analytics, eGIS, WLM, IHS and Enverus.

Understands basic data modeling and data integration principles and techniquesDetail oriented with ability to organize and synthesize large amounts of data to generate high-quality, executive-level quality presentations in an efficient mannerUnderstands E&P operations, non-operated business processes and drilling, completions, production, reservoir and geoscience data typesSelf-starter, with ability to work as part of a team or individuallyAdvanced written and verbal communication skillsAbility to quickly adapt and exemplify flexibility around process changes and shifting prioritiesAdvanced skills with data & analytics applicationsAdvanced knowledge of data modeling and data integration principles and techniquesAdvanced programming skills capable of using all available techniquesAction oriented - Taking on new opportunities and tough challenges with a sense of urgency, high energy, and enthusiasm.
Instills trust - Gaining the confidence and trust of others through honesty, integrity, and authenticity.
Ensures accountability - Holding self and others accountable to meet commitments.
Drives results - Consistently achieving results, even under tough circumstances.
Nimble learning - Actively learning through experimentation when tackling new problems, using both successes and failures as learning fodder.

Required Qualifications Minimum of eight (8) years' experience within the Oil and Gas industry working as a Data Analyst, Engineering Tech, Engineering Specialist, Business Analyst, Systems Analyst, IT Analyst or related roleAdvanced skills within Spotfire with the ability to use existing projects, inherit and enhance existing projects and create new projects from scratch leveraging multiple data sourcesAdvanced skills within SQL with the ability to retrieve data from systems, create integrated datasets using CTEs and/or subqueries, update data within systems and create data tables and views within CLR's data warehouseAn acceptable pre-employment background and drug test.

Intermediate skills developing automated workflows using UiPath, Grooper or AlteryxAdvanced coding skills in R or PythonPhysical Requirements and Working Conditions Requires prolonged sitting, some bending, and stooping.
Occasional lifting up to 25 pounds.

title: Director, Business Analysis and Insights - Talent Data
description:
Position Summary...

What you'll do...

DIRECTOR OF BUSINESS ANALYSIS AND INSIGHTS - TALENT DATA

The Why

A key Talent goal is to "cultivate an insights-driven Talent organization, enabling strategic talent decisions". This will be realized when delivery is based on the evaluation of the strategic needs of our business against our talent strategy and practices, in order to provide tailored, meaningful insights that are strategically embedded into our processes and ways of working.

The objective is to ensure that the right data is available at the right time, so that stakeholders can make data enabled decisions with confidence. As a result, we as an organization will drive better talent and business outcomes today, as well as for the future. In a market were digital evolution is a theme and competition for key talent is strong, a data driven talent culture is critical.

Responsibilities
â€¢ In this role, you will be responsible for leading the Talent Data Operations & Insights team, with the objective to elevate delivery through strategic partnership and customer driven products.
â€¢ As a leader, you will develop a delivery roadmap that supports the development, execution and improvement of overall Talent strategy to meet business needs.
â€¢ You will oversee a team focused on supporting aligned Talent Partners and Delivery leaders by providing relevant insights, and proactively highlighting wins, opportunities and risks with informed recommendations, analyzing complex data elements and developing data models that are easily digestible to help the team make best decisions based off the data, writing code, translating business problems to data related mathematical solutions.

Strategic Objectives
â€¢ Each Data Ops & Insights Partner will be responsible for elevating our delivery by proactively anticipating the needs of our stakeholders to deliver embedded insights that reduce the effort required to find, interpret, and use them.
â€¢ To do this, they will identify priorities and roadmap specific to the business that they support, determined through evaluation of our business strategy, the talent outcomes that we are driving towards it, and delivery of the right insights that will support achieving those outcomes.
â€¢ This will include incorporation of the necessary multiple internal data sources, as well as broadening the source of our inputs to include external data such as competitive intelligence and other market insights.
â€¢ By executing on their business roadmap, the Partner will enable their Talent team to become strategic advisors with the ability to directly impact business results.
â€¢ By the end of the year, their goal will be to have evolved a data driven talent culture, demonstrated by the successful integration of insights at the foundation of selected key talent and business decision and measured by KPIs grounded in our Talent experience and outcomes.
â€¢ As we enter this year, we can provide advanced analytics through descriptive and operational reporting with diagnostic analysis.
â€¢ Through the foundation we've laid with automation, historical data availability and the incorporation of market data, we are positioned to provide insight into current and future talent risks and opportunities, with emphasis on the likely outcomes and influences for our strategy and expect to be translating this to actionable guidance.

Delivery

The three primary offering types that the Partners will deliver are Consultancy, Analysis & Insights, Self-Serve Tools:

Consultancy
â€¢ Proactively identifying data and insight needs for strategy development and advising on development, execution and improvement of overall Talent strategy to meet business needs.
â€¢ Development of analysis and insight plan aligned to overall talent strategy in order to effectively inform and measure execution and effectiveness with regular alignment of forecast to actuals and updates based on influences, dynamic for ongoing decisions.
â€¢ Support aligned Talent Partners and Delivery leaders by providing relevant insights, and proactively highlighting wins, opportunities and risks with informed recommendations, identify performance standards and measure against them.
â€¢ Construct clear narrative and comms plan to inform decisions and directly or indirectly navigate related conversations with business and other critical stakeholders and presenting at key meetings.
â€¢ Apply domain expertise in business area (this includes complexities for that particular function related to hierarchy, cost centers, business rules, skills, org change, etc.), our internal data ecosystem (source, reliability), as well as inputs such as market insights and cross-functional data (this includes D and I, Campus, Military, Marketing, Sourcing, Executive, etc.) to deliver robust and reliable insights.
â€¢ As a partner embedded in the functional delivery team, building relationships within the team and business is critical.

Analysis and Insights
â€¢ Responsible for the delivery of complex analysis and insights supporting the strategic initiatives as well as providing input on actionable insights stemming from the below:
â€¢ Analytics related to ongoing strategy management and special/reoccurring project/initiative tracking.
â€¢ Root Cause/ROI Analysis (reporting to discover outcomes, drivers and influences). Develop and test hypothesis.
â€¢ Talent & Recruitment studies (internal and external insights to drive strategic change)
â€¢ Incorporation of diversity insights and data from pillars that run across model.
â€¢ Performance analysis against strategy, for internal use at team and recruiter level
â€¢ Quarterly business reviews
â€¢ Financial - cost per hire, with inputs specific to functional area, efficiencies
â€¢ Global Resource Model - capacity planning, weighting based on functional complexities.

Self-Serve Tools
â€¢ Developing scalable and repeatable suite of tools that meet business needs as well as consistency alignment across other functional groups to maximize efficiency and supplement delivery below partner level.
â€¢ Soliciting and incorporating customer feedback for continuous improvement and drive adoption.
â€¢ Translate requirements for tech teams into actional technical requirements with applicable knowledge of relevant data sets.

Education

In this role, you will influence leaders on how they can best leverage the available insights and build muscle throughout the team.

You will drive governance efforts which may include business process improvements to improve data outcomes as well as managing accountability and measuring progress against it through compliance reporting and other means.

Other Requirements: Location - Based in Bentonville, Arkansas

Comprehensive Relocation Package provided.

The above information has been designed to indicate the general nature and level of work performed in the role. It is not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities and qualifications required of employees assigned to this job. The full Job Description can be made available as part of the hiring process.

Benefits & Perks

Beyond competitive pay, you can receive incentive awards for your performance. Other great perks include 401(k) match, stock purchase plan, paid maternity and parental leave, PTO, multiple health plans, and much more.

Equal Opportunity Employer

Walmart, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer - By Choice. We believe we are best equipped to help our associates, customers and the communities we serve live better when we really know them. That means understanding, respecting and valuing diversity- unique styles, experiences, identities, ideas and opinions - while being inclusive of all people.

Who We Are

Join Walmart and your work could help over 275 million global customers live better every week. Yes, we are the Fortune #1 company. But you'll quickly find we're a company who wants you to feel comfortable bringing your whole self to work. A career at Walmart is where the world's most complex challenges meet a kinder way of life. Our mission spreads far beyond the walls of our stores. Join us and you'll discover why we are a world leader in diversity and inclusion, sustainability, and community involvement. From day one, you'll be empowered and equipped to do the best work of your life. careers.walmart.com

Minimum Qualifications...

Outlined below are the required minimum qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no minimum qualifications.

Minimum Qualifications Bachelor's degree in Business, Analytics, Statistics, or related field and 5 years' experience in data analytics, project management, business, or related area OR 7 years' experience in data analytics, project management, business, or related area. 3 years' experience using intermediate functionality of Microsoft Office. 4 years' supervisory experience.

Preferred Qualifications...

Outlined below are the optional preferred qualifications for this position. If none are listed, there are no preferred qualifications.

Consulting, Working on cross-functional teams or projects

Masters: Business

Project Management - Project Management Professional - Certification, Six Sigma - Certification
